http://schema.org/Thing.label: Thing
http://schema.org/Thing.comment: The most generic type of item.

properties.label: additionalType
properties.comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

properties.label: alternateName
properties.comment: An alias for the item.

properties.label: description
properties.comment: A short description of the item.

properties.label: image
properties.comment: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

properties.label: mainEntityOfPage
properties.comment:
Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described.

See background notes for details.

properties.label: name
properties.comment: The name of the item.

properties.label: sameAs
properties.comment: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Freebase page, or official website.

properties.label: url
properties.comment: URL of the item.

properties.label: potentialAction
properties.comment: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

http://schema.org/CreativeWork.label: CreativeWork
http://schema.org/CreativeWork.comment: The most generic kind of creative work, including books, movies, photographs, software programs, etc.

properties.label: schemaVersion
properties.comment: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using a URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

properties.label: about
properties.comment: The subject matter of the content.

properties.label: accessibilityAPI
properties.comment: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

properties.label: accessibilityControl
properties.comment: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

properties.label: accessibilityFeature
properties.comment: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

properties.label: accessibilityHazard
properties.comment: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

properties.label: accountablePerson
properties.comment: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: alternativeHeadline
properties.comment: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

properties.label: associatedMedia
properties.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

properties.label: audience
properties.comment: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

properties.label: audio
properties.comment: An embedded audio object.

properties.label: author
properties.comment: The author of this content. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

properties.label: award
properties.comment: An award won by or for this item.

properties.label: awards
properties.comment: Awards won by or for this item.

properties.label: citation
properties.comment: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

properties.label: comment
properties.comment: Comments, typically from users.

properties.label: contentLocation
properties.comment: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

properties.label: locationCreated
properties.comment: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

properties.label: contentRating
properties.comment: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

properties.label: contributor
properties.comment: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork.

properties.label: copyrightHolder
properties.comment: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

properties.label: copyrightYear
properties.comment: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

properties.label: creator
properties.comment: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

properties.label: dateCreated
properties.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

properties.label: dateModified
properties.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

properties.label: datePublished
properties.comment: Date of first broadcast/publication.

properties.label: discussionUrl
properties.comment: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

properties.label: editor
properties.comment: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

properties.label: educationalAlignment
properties.comment: An alignment to an established educational framework.

properties.label: educationalUse
properties.comment: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

properties.label: encoding
properties.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

properties.label: encodings
properties.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

properties.label: fileFormat
properties.comment: Media type (aka MIME format, see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information.

properties.label: genre
properties.comment: Genre of the creative work or group.

properties.label: headline
properties.comment: Headline of the article.

properties.label: inLanguage
properties.comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

properties.label: interactivityType
properties.comment: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

properties.label: isBasedOnUrl
properties.comment: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

properties.label: isFamilyFriendly
properties.comment: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

properties.label: isPartOf
properties.comment: Indicates a CreativeWork that this CreativeWork is (in some sense) part of.

properties.label: keywords
properties.comment: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

properties.label: license
properties.comment: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

properties.label: learningResourceType
properties.comment: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

properties.label: mainEntity
properties.comment: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

properties.label: mentions
properties.comment: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

properties.label: offers
properties.comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

properties.label: position
properties.comment: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

properties.label: producer
properties.comment: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

properties.label: publication
properties.comment: A publication event associated with the item.

properties.label: publisher
properties.comment: The publisher of the creative work.

properties.label: publishingPrinciples
properties.comment: Link to page describing the editorial principles of the organization primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

properties.label: recordedAt
properties.comment: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: reviews
properties.comment: Review of the item.

properties.label: sourceOrganization
properties.comment: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

properties.label: text
properties.comment: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

properties.label: thumbnailUrl
properties.comment: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

properties.label: timeRequired
properties.comment: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

properties.label: typicalAgeRange
properties.comment: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

properties.label: version
properties.comment: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

properties.label: video
properties.comment: An embedded video object.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

properties.label: commentCount
properties.comment: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

properties.label: hasPart
properties.comment: Indicates a CreativeWork that is (in some sense) a part of this CreativeWork.

properties.label: workExample
properties.comment: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

properties.label: exampleOfWork
properties.comment: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

properties.label: character
properties.comment: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

properties.label: translator
properties.comment: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market.

properties.label: releasedEvent
properties.comment: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

properties.label: interactionStatistic
properties.comment: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

http://schema.org/WebPage.label: WebPage
http://schema.org/WebPage.comment: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page.

properties.label: breadcrumb
properties.comment: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

properties.label: lastReviewed
properties.comment: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

properties.label: mainContentOfPage
properties.comment: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

properties.label: primaryImageOfPage
properties.comment: Indicates the main image on the page.

properties.label: relatedLink
properties.comment: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

properties.label: reviewedBy
properties.comment: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

properties.label: significantLink
properties.comment: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

properties.label: significantLinks
properties.comment: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

properties.label: specialty
properties.comment: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

http://schema.org/Organization.label: Organization
http://schema.org/Organization.comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

properties.label: hasOfferCatalog
properties.comment: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

properties.label: address
properties.comment: Physical address of the item.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: alumni
properties.comment: Alumni of an organization.

properties.label: areaServed
properties.comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

properties.label: award
properties.comment: An award won by or for this item.

properties.label: awards
properties.comment: Awards won by or for this item.

properties.label: parentOrganization
properties.comment: The larger organization that this organization is a branch of, if any.

properties.label: brand
properties.comment: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

properties.label: contactPoint
properties.comment: A contact point for a person or organization.

properties.label: contactPoints
properties.comment: A contact point for a person or organization.

properties.label: department
properties.comment: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

properties.label: duns
properties.comment: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

properties.label: email
properties.comment: Email address.

properties.label: employee
properties.comment: Someone working for this organization.

properties.label: employees
properties.comment: People working for this organization.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

properties.label: events
properties.comment: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

properties.label: faxNumber
properties.comment: The fax number.

properties.label: founder
properties.comment: A person who founded this organization.

properties.label: founders
properties.comment: A person who founded this organization.

properties.label: dissolutionDate
properties.comment: The date that this organization was dissolved.

properties.label: foundingDate
properties.comment: The date that this organization was founded.

properties.label: globalLocationNumber
properties.comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

properties.label: hasPOS
properties.comment: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

properties.label: isicV4
properties.comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

properties.label: legalName
properties.comment: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

properties.label: location
properties.comment: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

properties.label: logo
properties.comment: An associated logo.

properties.label: makesOffer
properties.comment: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

properties.label: member
properties.comment: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

properties.label: memberOf
properties.comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

properties.label: members
properties.comment: A member of this organization.

properties.label: naics
properties.comment: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

properties.label: numberOfEmployees
properties.comment: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

properties.label: owns
properties.comment: Products owned by the organization or person.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: reviews
properties.comment: Review of the item.

properties.label: seeks
properties.comment: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

properties.label: serviceArea
properties.comment: The geographic area where the service is provided.

properties.label: subOrganization
properties.comment: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

properties.label: taxID
properties.comment: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

properties.label: telephone
properties.comment: The telephone number.

properties.label: vatID
properties.comment: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

properties.label: foundingLocation
properties.comment: The place where the Organization was founded.

http://schema.org/Place.label: Place
http://schema.org/Place.comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

properties.label: address
properties.comment: Physical address of the item.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: branchCode
properties.comment:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

properties.label: containedInPlace
properties.comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

properties.label: containsPlace
properties.comment: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

properties.label: containedIn
properties.comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

properties.label: events
properties.comment: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

properties.label: faxNumber
properties.comment: The fax number.

properties.label: geo
properties.comment: The geo coordinates of the place.

properties.label: globalLocationNumber
properties.comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

properties.label: isicV4
properties.comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

properties.label: logo
properties.comment: An associated logo.

properties.label: hasMap
properties.comment: A URL to a map of the place.

properties.label: map
properties.comment: A URL to a map of the place.

properties.label: maps
properties.comment: A URL to a map of the place.

properties.label: openingHoursSpecification
properties.comment: The opening hours of a certain place.

properties.label: photo
properties.comment: A photograph of this place.

properties.label: photos
properties.comment: Photographs of this place.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: reviews
properties.comment: Review of the item.

properties.label: telephone
properties.comment: The telephone number.

properties.label: additionalProperty
properties.comment:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

http://schema.org/LocalBusiness.label: LocalBusiness
http://schema.org/LocalBusiness.comment: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

properties.label: branchOf
properties.comment: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any.

properties.label: branchCode
properties.comment:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

properties.label: currenciesAccepted
properties.comment: The currency accepted (in ISO 4217 currency format).

properties.label: openingHours
properties.comment:
The opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.
- Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
- Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
- Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
- If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

properties.label: paymentAccepted
properties.comment: Cash, credit card, etc.

properties.label: priceRange
properties.comment: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

http://schema.org/ProfessionalService.label: ProfessionalService
http://schema.org/ProfessionalService.comment:
Original definition: "provider of professional services."

The general ProfessionalService type for local businesses was deprecated due to confusion with Service. For reference, the types that it included were: Dentist, AccountingService, Attorney, Notary, as well as types for several kinds of HomeAndConstructionBusiness: Electrician, GeneralContractor, HousePainter, Locksmith, Plumber, RoofingContractor. LegalService was introduced as a more inclusive supertype of Attorney.

http://schema.org/LegalService.label: LegalService
http://schema.org/LegalService.comment:
A LegalService is a business that provides legally-oriented services, advice and representation, e.g. law firms.

As a LocalBusiness it can be described as a provider of one or more Service(s).

http://schema.org/AccountingService.label: AccountingService
http://schema.org/AccountingService.comment:
Accountancy business.

As a LocalBusiness it can be described as a provider of one or more Service(s).

http://schema.org/AdministrativeArea.label: AdministrativeArea
http://schema.org/AdministrativeArea.comment: A geographical region, typically under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

http://schema.org/Intangible.label: Intangible
http://schema.org/Intangible.comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

http://schema.org/Offer.label: Offer
http://schema.org/Offer.comment:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service—for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

For GTIN-related fields, see Check Digit calculator and validation guide from GS1.

properties.label: acceptedPaymentMethod
properties.comment: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

properties.label: addOn
properties.comment: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

properties.label: advanceBookingRequirement
properties.comment: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: areaServed
properties.comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

properties.label: availability
properties.comment: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

properties.label: availabilityEnds
properties.comment: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availabilityStarts
properties.comment: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availableAtOrFrom
properties.comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

properties.label: availableDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

properties.label: businessFunction
properties.comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

properties.label: category
properties.comment: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

properties.label: deliveryLeadTime
properties.comment: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods leaving the warehouse.

properties.label: eligibleCustomerType
properties.comment: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleDuration
properties.comment: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleQuantity
properties.comment: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

properties.label: eligibleRegion
properties.comment:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.

See also ineligibleRegion.

properties.label: ineligibleRegion
properties.comment:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.

See also eligibleRegion.

properties.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
properties.comment: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

properties.label: gtin12
properties.comment: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: gtin13
properties.comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: gtin14
properties.comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: gtin8
properties.comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: includesObject
properties.comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

properties.label: inventoryLevel
properties.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

properties.label: itemCondition
properties.comment: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

properties.label: itemOffered
properties.comment: The item being offered.

properties.label: offeredBy
properties.comment: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

properties.label: mpn
properties.comment: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: price
properties.comment:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:
  • Use the priceCurrency property (with ISO 4217 codes e.g. "USD") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

properties.label: priceSpecification
properties.comment: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

properties.label: priceValidUntil
properties.comment: The date after which the price is no longer available.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: reviews
properties.comment: Review of the item.

properties.label: seller
properties.comment: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

properties.label: serialNumber
properties.comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

properties.label: sku
properties.comment: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validThrough
properties.comment: The end of the validity of offer, price specification, or opening hours data.

properties.label: warranty
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

properties.label: priceCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

http://schema.org/AggregateOffer.label: AggregateOffer
http://schema.org/AggregateOffer.comment: When a single product is associated with multiple offers (for example, the same pair of shoes is offered by different merchants), then AggregateOffer can be used.

properties.label: highPrice
properties.comment: The highest price of all offers available.

properties.label: lowPrice
properties.comment: The lowest price of all offers available.

properties.label: offerCount
properties.comment: The number of offers for the product.

properties.label: offers
properties.comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

http://schema.org/Rating.label: Rating
http://schema.org/Rating.comment: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

properties.label: bestRating
properties.comment: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

properties.label: ratingValue
properties.comment: The rating for the content.

properties.label: worstRating
properties.comment: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

http://schema.org/AggregateRating.label: AggregateRating
http://schema.org/AggregateRating.comment: The average rating based on multiple ratings or reviews.

properties.label: itemReviewed
properties.comment: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

properties.label: ratingCount
properties.comment: The count of total number of ratings.

properties.label: reviewCount
properties.comment: The count of total number of reviews.

http://schema.org/CivicStructure.label: CivicStructure
http://schema.org/CivicStructure.comment: A public structure, such as a town hall or concert hall.

properties.label: openingHours
properties.comment:
The opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.
- Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
- Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
- Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
- If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

properties.label: iataCode
properties.comment: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

properties.label: iacoCode
properties.comment: IACO identifier for an airport.

http://schema.org/MedicalEntity.label: MedicalEntity
http://schema.org/MedicalEntity.comment: The most generic type of entity related to health and the practice of medicine.

properties.label: code
properties.comment: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

properties.label: guideline
properties.comment: A medical guideline related to this entity.

properties.label: medicineSystem
properties.comment: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

properties.label: recognizingAuthority
properties.comment: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

properties.label: relevantSpecialty
properties.comment: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

properties.label: study
properties.comment: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

http://schema.org/AnatomicalStructure.label: AnatomicalStructure
http://schema.org/AnatomicalStructure.comment: Any part of the human body, typically a component of an anatomical system. Organs, tissues, and cells are all anatomical structures.

properties.label: associatedPathophysiology
properties.comment: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

properties.label: bodyLocation
properties.comment: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

properties.label: connectedTo
properties.comment: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

properties.label: diagram
properties.comment: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

properties.label: function
properties.comment: Function of the anatomical structure.

properties.label: partOfSystem
properties.comment: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

properties.label: relatedCondition
properties.comment: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

properties.label: relatedTherapy
properties.comment: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

properties.label: subStructure
properties.comment: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

http://schema.org/AnatomicalSystem.label: AnatomicalSystem
http://schema.org/AnatomicalSystem.comment: An anatomical system is a group of anatomical structures that work together to perform a certain task. Anatomical systems, such as organ systems, are one organizing principle of anatomy, and can includes circulatory, digestive, endocrine, integumentary, immune, lymphatic, muscular, nervous, reproductive, respiratory, skeletal, urinary, vestibular, and other systems.

properties.label: associatedPathophysiology
properties.comment: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

properties.label: comprisedOf
properties.comment: The underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

properties.label: relatedCondition
properties.comment: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

properties.label: relatedStructure
properties.comment: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

properties.label: relatedTherapy
properties.comment: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

http://schema.org/Residence.label: Residence
http://schema.org/Residence.comment: The place where a person lives.

http://schema.org/MedicalIndication.label: MedicalIndication
http://schema.org/MedicalIndication.comment: A condition or factor that indicates use of a medical therapy, including signs, symptoms, risk factors, anatomical states, etc.

http://schema.org/ApprovedIndication.label: ApprovedIndication
http://schema.org/ApprovedIndication.comment: An indication for a medical therapy that has been formally specified or approved by a regulatory body that regulates use of the therapy; for example, the US FDA approves indications for most drugs in the US.

http://schema.org/Vessel.label: Vessel
http://schema.org/Vessel.comment: A component of the human body circulatory system comprised of an intricate network of hollow tubes that transport blood throughout the entire body.

http://schema.org/Artery.label: Artery
http://schema.org/Artery.comment: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood away from the heart.

properties.label: arterialBranch
properties.comment: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

properties.label: source
properties.comment: The anatomical or organ system that the artery originates from.

properties.label: supplyTo
properties.comment: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

http://schema.org/Article.label: Article
http://schema.org/Article.comment:
An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.

See also blog post.

properties.label: articleBody
properties.comment: The actual body of the article.

properties.label: articleSection
properties.comment: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

properties.label: wordCount
properties.comment: The number of words in the text of the Article.

properties.label: pageEnd
properties.comment: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

properties.label: pageStart
properties.comment: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

properties.label: pagination
properties.comment: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

http://schema.org/Report.label: Report
http://schema.org/Report.comment: A Report generated by governmental or non-governmental organization.

properties.label: reportNumber
properties.comment: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

http://schema.org/Attorney.label: Attorney
http://schema.org/Attorney.comment:
Professional service: Attorney.

This type is deprecated - LegalService is more inclusive and less ambiguous.

http://schema.org/Audience.label: Audience
http://schema.org/Audience.comment: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

properties.label: audienceType
properties.comment: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

properties.label: geographicArea
properties.comment: The geographic area associated with the audience.

http://schema.org/MediaObject.label: MediaObject
http://schema.org/MediaObject.comment: An image, video, or audio object embedded in a web page. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

properties.label: associatedArticle
properties.comment: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

properties.label: bitrate
properties.comment: The bitrate of the media object.

properties.label: contentSize
properties.comment: File size in (mega/kilo) bytes.

properties.label: contentUrl
properties.comment: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

properties.label: duration
properties.comment: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.

properties.label: embedUrl
properties.comment: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag.

properties.label: encodesCreativeWork
properties.comment: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

properties.label: encodingFormat
properties.comment: mp3, mpeg4, etc.

properties.label: expires
properties.comment: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. Useful for videos.

properties.label: height
properties.comment: The height of the item.

properties.label: playerType
properties.comment: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

properties.label: productionCompany
properties.comment: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

properties.label: regionsAllowed
properties.comment: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in ISO 3166 format.

properties.label: requiresSubscription
properties.comment: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription (either paid or free). Allowed values are true or false (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

properties.label: uploadDate
properties.comment: Date when this media object was uploaded to this site.

properties.label: width
properties.comment: The width of the item.

properties.label: transcript
properties.comment: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

properties.label: branchCode
properties.comment:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

properties.label: acceptsReservations
properties.comment: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, a URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings Yes or No.

properties.label: menu
properties.comment: Either the actual menu or a URL of the menu.

properties.label: servesCuisine
properties.comment: The cuisine of the restaurant.

http://schema.org/Barcode.label: Barcode
http://schema.org/Barcode.comment: An image of a visual machine-readable code such as a barcode or QR code.

http://schema.org/LodgingBusiness.label: LodgingBusiness
http://schema.org/LodgingBusiness.comment: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

properties.label: blogPost
properties.comment: A posting that is part of this blog.

properties.label: blogPosts
properties.comment: The postings that are part of this blog.

http://schema.org/MedicalTest.label: MedicalTest
http://schema.org/MedicalTest.comment: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

properties.label: affectedBy
properties.comment: Drugs that affect the test's results.

properties.label: normalRange
properties.comment: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

properties.label: signDetected
properties.comment: A sign detected by the test.

properties.label: usedToDiagnose
properties.comment: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

properties.label: usesDevice
properties.comment: Device used to perform the test.

http://schema.org/BloodTest.label: BloodTest
http://schema.org/BloodTest.comment: A medical test performed on a sample of a patient's blood.

http://schema.org/Landform.label: Landform
http://schema.org/Landform.comment: A landform or physical feature.  Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.

http://schema.org/BodyOfWater.label: BodyOfWater
http://schema.org/BodyOfWater.comment: A body of water, such as a sea, ocean, or lake.

http://schema.org/Bone.label: Bone
http://schema.org/Bone.comment: Rigid connective tissue that comprises up the skeletal structure of the human body.

properties.label: bookEdition
properties.comment: The edition of the book.

properties.label: bookFormat
properties.comment: The format of the book.

properties.label: illustrator
properties.comment: The illustrator of the book.

properties.label: isbn
properties.comment: The ISBN of the book.

properties.label: numberOfPages
properties.comment: The number of pages in the book.

http://schema.org/Enumeration.label: Enumeration
http://schema.org/Enumeration.comment: Lists or enumerations—for example, a list of cuisines or music genres, etc.

properties.label: supersededBy
properties.comment: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

http://schema.org/BookFormatType.label: BookFormatType
http://schema.org/BookFormatType.comment: The publication format of the book.

http://schema.org/DataType.label: DataType
http://schema.org/DataType.comment: The basic data types such as Integers, Strings, etc.

http://schema.org/SportsActivityLocation.label: SportsActivityLocation
http://schema.org/SportsActivityLocation.comment: A sports location, such as a playing field.

http://schema.org/BrainStructure.label: BrainStructure
http://schema.org/BrainStructure.comment: Any anatomical structure which pertains to the soft nervous tissue functioning as the coordinating center of sensation and intellectual and nervous activity.

http://schema.org/PlaceOfWorship.label: PlaceOfWorship
http://schema.org/PlaceOfWorship.comment: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.

http://schema.org/Event.label: Event
http://schema.org/Event.comment: An event happening at a certain time and location, such as a concert, lecture, or festival. Ticketing information may be added via the 'offers' property. Repeated events may be structured as separate Event objects.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: organizer
properties.comment: An organizer of an Event.

properties.label: attendee
properties.comment: A person or organization attending the event.

properties.label: attendees
properties.comment: A person attending the event.

properties.label: doorTime
properties.comment: The time admission will commence.

properties.label: duration
properties.comment: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.

properties.label: endDate
properties.comment: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

properties.label: eventStatus
properties.comment: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

properties.label: inLanguage
properties.comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

properties.label: location
properties.comment: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

properties.label: offers
properties.comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

properties.label: performer
properties.comment: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

properties.label: performers
properties.comment: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

properties.label: previousStartDate
properties.comment: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

properties.label: recordedIn
properties.comment: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: startDate
properties.comment: The start date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

properties.label: subEvent
properties.comment: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

properties.label: subEvents
properties.comment: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

properties.label: superEvent
properties.comment: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

properties.label: typicalAgeRange
properties.comment: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

properties.label: workPerformed
properties.comment: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

properties.label: workFeatured
properties.comment:
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.
       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

http://schema.org/Canal.label: Canal
http://schema.org/Canal.comment: A canal, like the Panama Canal.

properties.label: alumni
properties.comment: Alumni of an organization.

http://schema.org/CollegeOrUniversity.label: CollegeOrUniversity
http://schema.org/CollegeOrUniversity.comment: A college, university, or other third-level educational institution.

http://schema.org/Comment.label: Comment
http://schema.org/Comment.comment: A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment's content is expressed via the "text" property, and its topic via "about", properties shared with all CreativeWorks.

properties.label: upvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

properties.label: downvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

properties.label: parentItem
properties.comment: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

http://schema.org/StructuredValue.label: StructuredValue
http://schema.org/StructuredValue.comment: Structured values are used when the value of a property has a more complex structure than simply being a textual value or a reference to another thing.

http://schema.org/ContactPoint.label: ContactPoint
http://schema.org/ContactPoint.comment: A contact point—for example, a Customer Complaints department.

properties.label: areaServed
properties.comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

properties.label: availableLanguage
properties.comment: A language someone may use with the item.

properties.label: contactOption
properties.comment: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

properties.label: contactType
properties.comment: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

properties.label: email
properties.comment: Email address.

properties.label: faxNumber
properties.comment: The fax number.

properties.label: hoursAvailable
properties.comment: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

properties.label: productSupported
properties.comment: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

properties.label: serviceArea
properties.comment: The geographic area where the service is provided.

properties.label: telephone
properties.comment: The telephone number.

http://schema.org/Continent.label: Continent
http://schema.org/Continent.comment: One of the continents (for example, Europe or Africa).

properties.label: tickerSymbol
properties.comment: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we reccommend using the controlled vocaulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO15022.

http://schema.org/MedicalIntangible.label: MedicalIntangible
http://schema.org/MedicalIntangible.comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things in the medical space.

http://schema.org/DDxElement.label: DDxElement
http://schema.org/DDxElement.comment: An alternative, closely-related condition typically considered later in the differential diagnosis process along with the signs that are used to distinguish it.

properties.label: diagnosis
properties.comment: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process.

properties.label: distinguishingSign
properties.comment: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

http://schema.org/PerformingGroup.label: PerformingGroup
http://schema.org/PerformingGroup.comment: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

http://schema.org/DanceGroup.label: DanceGroup
http://schema.org/DanceGroup.comment: A dance group—for example, the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater or Riverdance.

http://schema.org/DefenceEstablishment.label: DefenceEstablishment
http://schema.org/DefenceEstablishment.comment: A defence establishment, such as an army or navy base.

http://schema.org/MedicalOrganization.label: MedicalOrganization
http://schema.org/MedicalOrganization.comment: A medical organization, such as a doctor's office or clinic.

http://schema.org/DiagnosticLab.label: DiagnosticLab
http://schema.org/DiagnosticLab.comment: A medical laboratory that offers on-site or off-site diagnostic services.

properties.label: availableTest
properties.comment: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

http://schema.org/MedicalProcedure.label: MedicalProcedure
http://schema.org/MedicalProcedure.comment: A process of care used in either a diagnostic, therapeutic, or palliative capacity that relies on invasive (surgical), non-invasive, or percutaneous techniques.

properties.label: followup
properties.comment: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

properties.label: howPerformed
properties.comment: How the procedure is performed.

properties.label: preparation
properties.comment: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

properties.label: procedureType
properties.comment: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

http://schema.org/DiagnosticProcedure.label: DiagnosticProcedure
http://schema.org/DiagnosticProcedure.comment: A medical procedure intended primarily for diagnostic, as opposed to therapeutic, purposes.

http://schema.org/MedicalTherapy.label: MedicalTherapy
http://schema.org/MedicalTherapy.comment: Any medical intervention designed to prevent, treat, and cure human diseases and medical conditions, including both curative and palliative therapies. Medical therapies are typically processes of care relying upon pharmacotherapy, behavioral therapy, supportive therapy (with fluid or nutrition for example), or detoxification (e.g. hemodialysis) aimed at improving or preventing a health condition.

properties.label: adverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.

properties.label: contraindication
properties.comment: A contraindication for this therapy.

properties.label: duplicateTherapy
properties.comment: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

properties.label: indication
properties.comment: A factor that indicates use of this therapy for treatment and/or prevention of a condition, symptom, etc. For therapies such as drugs, indications can include both officially-approved indications as well as off-label uses. These can be distinguished by using the ApprovedIndication subtype of MedicalIndication.

properties.label: seriousAdverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

http://schema.org/LifestyleModification.label: LifestyleModification
http://schema.org/LifestyleModification.comment: A process of care involving exercise, changes to diet, fitness routines, and other lifestyle changes aimed at improving a health condition.

http://schema.org/Diet.label: Diet
http://schema.org/Diet.comment: A strategy of regulating the intake of food to achieve or maintain a specific health-related goal.

properties.label: dietFeatures
properties.comment: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

properties.label: endorsers
properties.comment: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

properties.label: expertConsiderations
properties.comment: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

properties.label: overview
properties.comment: Descriptive information establishing the overarching theory/philosophy of the plan. May include the rationale for the name, the population where the plan first came to prominence, etc.

properties.label: physiologicalBenefits
properties.comment: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

properties.label: proprietaryName
properties.comment: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

properties.label: risks
properties.comment: Specific physiologic risks associated to the plan.

http://schema.org/DietarySupplement.label: DietarySupplement
http://schema.org/DietarySupplement.comment: A product taken by mouth that contains a dietary ingredient intended to supplement the diet. Dietary ingredients may include vitamins, minerals, herbs or other botanicals, amino acids, and substances such as enzymes, organ tissues, glandulars and metabolites.

properties.label: activeIngredient
properties.comment: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

properties.label: background
properties.comment: Descriptive information establishing a historical perspective on the supplement. May include the rationale for the name, the population where the supplement first came to prominence, etc.

properties.label: dosageForm
properties.comment: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

properties.label: isProprietary
properties.comment: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

properties.label: legalStatus
properties.comment: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

properties.label: manufacturer
properties.comment: The manufacturer of the product.

properties.label: maximumIntake
properties.comment: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

properties.label: mechanismOfAction
properties.comment: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

properties.label: nonProprietaryName
properties.comment: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

properties.label: recommendedIntake
properties.comment: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

properties.label: safetyConsideration
properties.comment: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

properties.label: targetPopulation
properties.comment: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

http://schema.org/Quantity.label: Quantity
http://schema.org/Quantity.comment: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 Kg' or '4 milligrams'.

http://schema.org/Distance.label: Distance
http://schema.org/Distance.comment: Properties that take Distances as values are of the form '<Number> <Length unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 ft'.

http://schema.org/DoseSchedule.label: DoseSchedule
http://schema.org/DoseSchedule.comment: A specific dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

properties.label: doseUnit
properties.comment: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

properties.label: doseValue
properties.comment: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

properties.label: frequency
properties.comment: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

properties.label: targetPopulation
properties.comment: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

http://schema.org/Drug.label: Drug
http://schema.org/Drug.comment: A chemical or biologic substance, used as a medical therapy, that has a physiological effect on an organism.

properties.label: activeIngredient
properties.comment: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

properties.label: administrationRoute
properties.comment: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

properties.label: alcoholWarning
properties.comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

properties.label: availableStrength
properties.comment: An available dosage strength for the drug.

properties.label: breastfeedingWarning
properties.comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

properties.label: clinicalPharmacology
properties.comment: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

properties.label: clinicalPharmacology
properties.comment: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

properties.label: cost
properties.comment: Cost per unit of the drug, as reported by the source being tagged.

properties.label: dosageForm
properties.comment: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

properties.label: doseSchedule
properties.comment: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

properties.label: drugClass
properties.comment: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

properties.label: foodWarning
properties.comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

properties.label: interactingDrug
properties.comment: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

properties.label: isAvailableGenerically
properties.comment: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

properties.label: isProprietary
properties.comment: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

properties.label: labelDetails
properties.comment: Link to the drug's label details.

properties.label: legalStatus
properties.comment: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

properties.label: manufacturer
properties.comment: The manufacturer of the product.

properties.label: mechanismOfAction
properties.comment: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

properties.label: nonProprietaryName
properties.comment: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

properties.label: overdosage
properties.comment: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

properties.label: pregnancyCategory
properties.comment: Pregnancy category of this drug.

properties.label: pregnancyWarning
properties.comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

properties.label: prescribingInfo
properties.comment: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

properties.label: prescriptionStatus
properties.comment: Indicates whether this drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter.

properties.label: relatedDrug
properties.comment: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

properties.label: warning
properties.comment: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

http://schema.org/DrugClass.label: DrugClass
http://schema.org/DrugClass.comment: A class of medical drugs, e.g., statins. Classes can represent general pharmacological class, common mechanisms of action, common physiological effects, etc.

properties.label: drug
properties.comment: A drug in this drug class.

http://schema.org/DrugCost.label: DrugCost
http://schema.org/DrugCost.comment: The cost per unit of a medical drug. Note that this type is not meant to represent the price in an offer of a drug for sale; see the Offer type for that. This type will typically be used to tag wholesale or average retail cost of a drug, or maximum reimbursable cost. Costs of medical drugs vary widely depending on how and where they are paid for, so while this type captures some of the variables, costs should be used with caution by consumers of this schema's markup.

properties.label: applicableLocation
properties.comment: The location in which the status applies.

properties.label: costCategory
properties.comment: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

properties.label: costCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the drug cost.

properties.label: costOrigin
properties.comment: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

properties.label: costPerUnit
properties.comment: The cost per unit of the drug.

properties.label: drugUnit
properties.comment: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

http://schema.org/MedicalEnumeration.label: MedicalEnumeration
http://schema.org/MedicalEnumeration.comment: Enumerations related to health and the practice of medicine.

http://schema.org/DrugCostCategory.label: DrugCostCategory
http://schema.org/DrugCostCategory.comment: Enumerated categories of medical drug costs.

http://schema.org/DrugLegalStatus.label: DrugLegalStatus
http://schema.org/DrugLegalStatus.comment: The legal availability status of a medical drug.

properties.label: applicableLocation
properties.comment: The location in which the status applies.

http://schema.org/DrugPregnancyCategory.label: DrugPregnancyCategory
http://schema.org/DrugPregnancyCategory.comment: Categories that represent an assessment of the risk of fetal injury due to a drug or pharmaceutical used as directed by the mother during pregnancy.

http://schema.org/DrugPrescriptionStatus.label: DrugPrescriptionStatus
http://schema.org/DrugPrescriptionStatus.comment: Indicates whether this drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter.

http://schema.org/DrugStrength.label: DrugStrength
http://schema.org/DrugStrength.comment: A specific strength in which a medical drug is available in a specific country.

properties.label: activeIngredient
properties.comment: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

properties.label: availableIn
properties.comment: The location in which the strength is available.

properties.label: strengthUnit
properties.comment: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

properties.label: strengthValue
properties.comment: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

http://schema.org/HomeAndConstructionBus.label: HomeAndConstructionBusiness
http://schema.org/HomeAndConstructionBus.comment:
A construction business.

A HomeAndConstructionBusiness is a LocalBusiness that provides services around homes and buildings.

As a LocalBusiness it can be described as a provider of one or more Service(s).

http://schema.org/EmergencyService.label: EmergencyService
http://schema.org/EmergencyService.comment: An emergency service, such as a fire station or ER.

http://schema.org/Energy.label: Energy
http://schema.org/Energy.comment: Properties that take Energy as values are of the form '<Number> <Energy unit of measure>'.

http://schema.org/PhysicalActivity.label: PhysicalActivity
http://schema.org/PhysicalActivity.comment: Any bodily activity that enhances or maintains physical fitness and overall health and wellness. Includes activity that is part of daily living and routine, structured exercise, and exercise prescribed as part of a medical treatment or recovery plan.

properties.label: associatedAnatomy
properties.comment: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

properties.label: category
properties.comment: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

properties.label: epidemiology
properties.comment: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

properties.label: pathophysiology
properties.comment: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

http://schema.org/ExercisePlan.label: ExercisePlan
http://schema.org/ExercisePlan.comment: Fitness-related activity designed for a specific health-related purpose, including defined exercise routines as well as activity prescribed by a clinician.

properties.label: activityDuration
properties.comment: Length of time to engage in the activity.

properties.label: activityFrequency
properties.comment: How often one should engage in the activity.

properties.label: additionalVariable
properties.comment: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.

properties.label: exerciseType
properties.comment: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

properties.label: intensity
properties.comment: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

properties.label: repetitions
properties.comment: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

properties.label: restPeriods
properties.comment: How often one should break from the activity.

properties.label: workload
properties.comment: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

http://schema.org/GeoCoordinates.label: GeoCoordinates
http://schema.org/GeoCoordinates.comment: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

properties.label: address
properties.comment: Physical address of the item.

properties.label: addressCountry
properties.comment: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

properties.label: elevation
properties.comment: The elevation of a location (WGS 84).

properties.label: latitude
properties.comment: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

properties.label: longitude
properties.comment: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

properties.label: postalCode
properties.comment: The postal code. For example, 94043.

http://schema.org/GeoShape.label: GeoShape
http://schema.org/GeoShape.comment: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.

properties.label: address
properties.comment: Physical address of the item.

properties.label: addressCountry
properties.comment: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

properties.label: box
properties.comment: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

properties.label: circle
properties.comment: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

properties.label: elevation
properties.comment: The elevation of a location (WGS 84).

properties.label: line
properties.comment: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

properties.label: polygon
properties.comment: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

properties.label: postalCode
properties.comment: The postal code. For example, 94043.

http://schema.org/GeoCircle.label: GeoCircle
http://schema.org/GeoCircle.comment:
A GeoCircle is a GeoShape representing a circular geographic area. As it is a GeoShape
          it provides the simple textual property 'circle', but also allows the combination of postalCode alongside geoRadius.
          The center of the circle can be indicated via the 'geoMidpoint' property, or more approximately using 'address', 'postalCode'.

properties.label: geoRadius
properties.comment: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

properties.label: geoMidpoint
properties.comment: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.

http://schema.org/GovernmentOffice.label: GovernmentOffice
http://schema.org/GovernmentOffice.comment: A government office—for example, an IRS or DMV office.

http://schema.org/HVACBusiness.label: HVACBusiness
http://schema.org/HVACBusiness.comment: A business that provide Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning services.

http://schema.org/HobbyShop.label: HobbyShop
