http://schema.org/HobbyShop.comment: A store that sells materials useful or necessary for various hobbies.

properties.label: availableService
properties.comment: A medical service available from this provider.

properties.label: medicalSpecialty
properties.comment: A medical specialty of the provider.

http://schema.org/Hostel.label: Hostel
http://schema.org/Hostel.comment: A hostel - cheap accommodation, often in shared dormitories.

http://schema.org/ImageGallery.label: ImageGallery
http://schema.org/ImageGallery.comment: Web page type: Image gallery page.

properties.label: caption
properties.comment: The caption for this object.

properties.label: exifData
properties.comment: exif data for this object.

properties.label: representativeOfPage
properties.comment: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

properties.label: thumbnail
properties.comment: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

http://schema.org/ImagingTest.label: ImagingTest
http://schema.org/ImagingTest.comment: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes.

properties.label: imagingTechnique
properties.comment: Imaging technique used.

http://schema.org/InfectiousAgentClass.label: InfectiousAgentClass
http://schema.org/InfectiousAgentClass.comment: Classes of agents or pathogens that transmit infectious diseases. Enumerated type.

http://schema.org/MedicalCondition.label: MedicalCondition
http://schema.org/MedicalCondition.comment: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.

properties.label: associatedAnatomy
properties.comment: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

properties.label: cause
properties.comment: An underlying cause. More specifically, one of the causative agent(s) that are most directly responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in the occurrence.

properties.label: differentialDiagnosis
properties.comment: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

properties.label: epidemiology
properties.comment: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

properties.label: expectedPrognosis
properties.comment: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

properties.label: naturalProgression
properties.comment: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

properties.label: pathophysiology
properties.comment: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

properties.label: possibleComplication
properties.comment: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

properties.label: possibleTreatment
properties.comment: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

properties.label: primaryPrevention
properties.comment: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

properties.label: riskFactor
properties.comment: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

properties.label: secondaryPrevention
properties.comment: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

properties.label: signOrSymptom
properties.comment: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

properties.label: stage
properties.comment: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

properties.label: subtype
properties.comment: A more specific type of the condition, where applicable, for example 'Type 1 Diabetes', 'Type 2 Diabetes', or 'Gestational Diabetes' for Diabetes.

properties.label: typicalTest
properties.comment: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

http://schema.org/InfectiousDisease.label: InfectiousDisease
http://schema.org/InfectiousDisease.comment: An infectious disease is a clinically evident human disease resulting from the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, like pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and prions. To be considered an infectious disease, such pathogens are known to be able to cause this disease.

properties.label: infectiousAgent
properties.comment: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

properties.label: infectiousAgentClass
properties.comment: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

properties.label: transmissionMethod
properties.comment: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

http://schema.org/ItemAvailability.label: ItemAvailability
http://schema.org/ItemAvailability.comment: A list of possible product availability options.

http://schema.org/ItemList.label: ItemList
http://schema.org/ItemList.comment: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

properties.label: numberOfItems
properties.comment: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

properties.label: itemListOrder
properties.comment: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

properties.label: itemListElement
properties.comment:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

http://schema.org/BreadcrumbList.label: BreadcrumbList
http://schema.org/BreadcrumbList.comment:
A BreadcrumbList is an ItemList consisting of a chain of linked Web pages, typically described using at least their URL and their name, and typically ending with the current page.

The 'position' property is used to reconstruct the order of the items in a BreadcrumbList. The convention is that a breadcrumb list has an itemListOrder of ItemListOrderAscending (lower values listed first), and that the first items in this list correspond to the "top" or beginning of the breadcrumb trail, e.g. with a site or section homepage. The specific values of 'position' are not assigned meaning for a BreadcrumbList, but they should be integers, e.g. beginning with '1' for the first item in the list.

http://schema.org/OfferCatalog.label: OfferCatalog
http://schema.org/OfferCatalog.comment: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

http://schema.org/ItemPage.label: ItemPage
http://schema.org/ItemPage.comment: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.

http://schema.org/JobPosting.label: JobPosting
http://schema.org/JobPosting.comment: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

properties.label: baseSalary
properties.comment: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

properties.label: benefits
properties.comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.

properties.label: jobBenefits
properties.comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.

properties.label: datePosted
properties.comment: Publication date for the job posting.

properties.label: educationRequirements
properties.comment: Educational background needed for the position.

properties.label: employmentType
properties.comment: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

properties.label: experienceRequirements
properties.comment: Description of skills and experience needed for the position.

properties.label: hiringOrganization
properties.comment: Organization offering the job position.

properties.label: incentives
properties.comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

properties.label: incentiveCompensation
properties.comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

properties.label: industry
properties.comment: The industry associated with the job position.

properties.label: jobLocation
properties.comment: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

properties.label: occupationalCategory
properties.comment: Category or categories describing the job. Use BLS O*NET-SOC taxonomy: http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html. Ideally includes textual label and formal code, with the property repeated for each applicable value.

properties.label: qualifications
properties.comment: Specific qualifications required for this role.

properties.label: responsibilities
properties.comment: Responsibilities associated with this role.

properties.label: salaryCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (coded using ISO 4217, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217 ) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

properties.label: skills
properties.comment: Skills required to fulfill this role.

properties.label: specialCommitments
properties.comment: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

properties.label: title
properties.comment: The title of the job.

properties.label: workHours
properties.comment: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

http://schema.org/Joint.label: Joint
http://schema.org/Joint.comment: The anatomical location at which two or more bones make contact.

properties.label: biomechnicalClass
properties.comment: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

properties.label: functionalClass
properties.comment: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

properties.label: structuralClass
properties.comment: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

http://schema.org/Language.label: Language
http://schema.org/Language.comment: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. and programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp.

http://schema.org/LegislativeBuilding.label: LegislativeBuilding
http://schema.org/LegislativeBuilding.comment: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

http://schema.org/Ligament.label: Ligament
http://schema.org/Ligament.comment: A short band of tough, flexible, fibrous connective tissue that functions to connect multiple bones, cartilages, and structurally support joints.

http://schema.org/LiquorStore.label: LiquorStore
http://schema.org/LiquorStore.comment: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.

http://schema.org/LymphaticVessel.label: LymphaticVessel
http://schema.org/LymphaticVessel.comment: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries lymph fluid unidirectionally toward the heart.

properties.label: originatesFrom
properties.comment: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

properties.label: regionDrained
properties.comment: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

properties.label: runsTo
properties.comment: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

properties.label: mapType
properties.comment: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

http://schema.org/MapCategoryType.label: MapCategoryType
http://schema.org/MapCategoryType.comment: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.

http://schema.org/Mass.label: Mass
http://schema.org/Mass.comment: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.

http://schema.org/MaximumDoseSchedule.label: MaximumDoseSchedule
http://schema.org/MaximumDoseSchedule.comment: The maximum dosing schedule considered safe for a drug or supplement as recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

http://schema.org/PeopleAudience.label: PeopleAudience
http://schema.org/PeopleAudience.comment: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

properties.label: healthCondition
properties.comment: Expectations for health conditions of target audience.

properties.label: requiredGender
properties.comment: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

properties.label: requiredMaxAge
properties.comment: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

properties.label: requiredMinAge
properties.comment: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

properties.label: suggestedGender
properties.comment: The gender of the person or audience.

properties.label: suggestedMaxAge
properties.comment: Maximal age recommended for viewing content.

properties.label: suggestedMinAge
properties.comment: Minimal age recommended for viewing content.

http://schema.org/MedicalAudience.label: MedicalAudience
http://schema.org/MedicalAudience.comment: Target audiences for medical web pages. Enumerated type.

http://schema.org/MedicalCause.label: MedicalCause
http://schema.org/MedicalCause.comment:
The causative agent(s) that are responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in a medical condition, symptom or sign. In this schema, unless otherwise specified this is meant to be the proximate cause of the medical condition, symptom or sign. The proximate cause is defined as the causative agent that most directly results in the medical condition, symptom or sign. For example, the HIV virus could be considered a cause of AIDS. Or in a diagnostic context, if a patient fell and sustained a hip fracture and two days later sustained a pulmonary embolism which eventuated in a cardiac arrest, the cause of the cardiac arrest (the proximate cause) would be the pulmonary embolism and not the fall.

Medical causes can include cardiovascular, chemical, dermatologic, endocrine, environmental, gastroenterologic, genetic, hematologic, gynecologic, iatrogenic, infectious, musculoskeletal, neurologic, nutritional, obstetric, oncologic, otolaryngologic, pharmacologic, psychiatric, pulmonary, renal, rheumatologic, toxic, traumatic, or urologic causes; medical conditions can be causes as well.

properties.label: causeOf
properties.comment: The condition, complication, symptom, sign, etc. caused.

properties.label: availableService
properties.comment: A medical service available from this provider.

properties.label: medicalSpecialty
properties.comment: A medical specialty of the provider.

http://schema.org/MedicalCode.label: MedicalCode
http://schema.org/MedicalCode.comment: A code for a medical entity.

properties.label: codeValue
properties.comment: The actual code.

properties.label: codingSystem
properties.comment: The coding system, e.g. 'ICD-10'.

http://schema.org/MedicalConditionStage.label: MedicalConditionStage
http://schema.org/MedicalConditionStage.comment: A stage of a medical condition, such as 'Stage IIIa'.

properties.label: stageAsNumber
properties.comment: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

properties.label: subStageSuffix
properties.comment: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

http://schema.org/MedicalContraindicatio.label: MedicalContraindication
http://schema.org/MedicalContraindicatio.comment: A condition or factor that serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical therapy. Contraindications can be absolute (there are no reasonable circumstances for undertaking a course of action) or relative (the patient is at higher risk of complications, but that these risks may be outweighed by other considerations or mitigated by other measures).

http://schema.org/MedicalDevice.label: MedicalDevice
http://schema.org/MedicalDevice.comment: Any object used in a medical capacity, such as to diagnose or treat a patient.

properties.label: adverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.

properties.label: contraindication
properties.comment: A contraindication for this therapy.

properties.label: indication
properties.comment: A factor that indicates use of this therapy for treatment and/or prevention of a condition, symptom, etc. For therapies such as drugs, indications can include both officially-approved indications as well as off-label uses. These can be distinguished by using the ApprovedIndication subtype of MedicalIndication.

properties.label: postOp
properties.comment: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

properties.label: preOp
properties.comment: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

properties.label: procedure
properties.comment: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

properties.label: purpose
properties.comment: A goal towards an action is taken. Can be concrete or abstract.

properties.label: seriousAdverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

http://schema.org/MedicalDevicePurpose.label: MedicalDevicePurpose
http://schema.org/MedicalDevicePurpose.comment: Categories of medical devices, organized by the purpose or intended use of the device.

http://schema.org/MedicalEvidenceLevel.label: MedicalEvidenceLevel
http://schema.org/MedicalEvidenceLevel.comment: Level of evidence for a medical guideline. Enumerated type.

http://schema.org/MedicalGuideline.label: MedicalGuideline
http://schema.org/MedicalGuideline.comment: Any recommendation made by a standard society (e.g. ACC/AHA) or consensus statement that denotes how to diagnose and treat a particular condition. Note: this type should be used to tag the actual guideline recommendation; if the guideline recommendation occurs in a larger scholarly article, use MedicalScholarlyArticle to tag the overall article, not this type. Note also: the organization making the recommendation should be captured in the recognizingAuthority base property of MedicalEntity.

properties.label: evidenceLevel
properties.comment: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

properties.label: evidenceOrigin
properties.comment: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

properties.label: guidelineDate
properties.comment: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

properties.label: guidelineSubject
properties.comment: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

http://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineContra.label: MedicalGuidelineContraindication
http://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineContra.comment: A guideline contraindication that designates a process as harmful and where quality of the data supporting the contraindication is sound.

http://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineRecomm.label: MedicalGuidelineRecommendation
http://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineRecomm.comment: A guideline recommendation that is regarded as efficacious and where quality of the data supporting the recommendation is sound.

properties.label: recommendationStrength
properties.comment: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

http://schema.org/MedicalImagingTechniqu.label: MedicalImagingTechnique
http://schema.org/MedicalImagingTechniqu.comment: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes. Enumerated type.

http://schema.org/MedicalStudy.label: MedicalStudy
http://schema.org/MedicalStudy.comment: A medical study is an umbrella type covering all kinds of research studies relating to human medicine or health, including observational studies and interventional trials and registries, randomized, controlled or not. When the specific type of study is known, use one of the extensions of this type, such as MedicalTrial or MedicalObservationalStudy. Also, note that this type should be used to mark up data that describes the study itself; to tag an article that publishes the results of a study, use MedicalScholarlyArticle. http://schema.org/SuperficialAnatomy.label: SuperficialAnatomy
http://schema.org/SuperficialAnatomy.comment: Anatomical features that can be observed by sight (without dissection), including the form and proportions of the human body as well as surface landmarks that correspond to deeper subcutaneous structures. Superficial anatomy plays an important role in sports medicine, phlebotomy, and other medical specialties as underlying anatomical structures can be identified through surface palpation. For example, during back surgery, superficial anatomy can be used to palpate and count vertebrae to find the site of incision. Or in phlebotomy, superficial anatomy can be used to locate an underlying vein; for example, the median cubital vein can be located by palpating the borders of the cubital fossa (such as the epicondyles of the humerus) and then looking for the superficial signs of the vein, such as size, prominence, ability to refill after depression, and feel of surrounding tissue support. As another example, in a subluxation (dislocation) of the glenohumeral joint, the bony structure becomes pronounced with the deltoid muscle failing to cover the glenohumeral joint allowing the edges of the scapula to be superficially visible. Here, the superficial anatomy is the visible edges of the scapula, implying the underlying dislocation of the joint (the related anatomical structure).

http://schema.org/CreativeWorkSeries.label: CreativeWorkSeries
http://schema.org/CreativeWorkSeries.comment:
A CreativeWorkSeries in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. CreativeWorkSeries are usually organized into some order, often chronological. Unlike ItemList which is a general purpose data structure for lists of things, the emphasis with CreativeWorkSeries is on published materials (written e.g. books and periodicals, or media such as tv, radio and games).

Specific subtypes are available for describing TVSeries, RadioSeries, MovieSeries, BookSeries, Periodical and VideoGameSeries. In each case, the hasPart / isPartOf properties can be used to relate the CreativeWorkSeries to its parts. The general CreativeWorkSeries type serves largely just to organize these more specific and practical subtypes.

It is common for properties applicable to an item from the series to be usefully applied to the containing group. Schema.org attempts to anticipate some of these cases, but publishers should be free to apply properties of the series parts to the series as a whole wherever they seem appropriate.

The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.

See also eligibleRegion.

http://schema.org/DeliveryMethod.label: DeliveryMethod
http://schema.org/DeliveryMethod.comment:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfillment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.
Commonly used values:

http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeMail
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeOwnFleet
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModePickUp
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

http://schema.org/Demand.label: Demand
http://schema.org/Demand.comment: A demand entity represents the public, not necessarily binding, not necessarily exclusive, announcement by an organization or person to seek a certain type of goods or services. For describing demand using this type, the very same properties used for Offer apply.

properties.label: acceptedPaymentMethod
properties.comment: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

properties.label: advanceBookingRequirement
properties.comment: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

properties.label: areaServed
properties.comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

properties.label: availability
properties.comment: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

properties.label: availabilityEnds
properties.comment: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availabilityStarts
properties.comment: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availableAtOrFrom
properties.comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

properties.label: availableDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

properties.label: businessFunction
properties.comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

properties.label: deliveryLeadTime
properties.comment: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods leaving the warehouse.

properties.label: eligibleCustomerType
properties.comment: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleDuration
properties.comment: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleQuantity
properties.comment: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

properties.label: eligibleRegion
properties.comment:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.

See also ineligibleRegion.

properties.label: ineligibleRegion
properties.comment:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.

See also eligibleRegion.

properties.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
properties.comment: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

properties.label: gtin12
properties.comment: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: gtin13
properties.comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: gtin14
properties.comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: gtin8
properties.comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

properties.label: includesObject
properties.comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

properties.label: inventoryLevel
properties.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

properties.label: itemCondition
properties.comment: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

properties.label: itemOffered
properties.comment: The item being offered.

properties.label: mpn
properties.comment: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: priceSpecification
properties.comment: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

properties.label: seller
properties.comment: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

properties.label: serialNumber
properties.comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

properties.label: sku
properties.comment: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validThrough
properties.comment: The end of the validity of offer, price specification, or opening hours data.

properties.label: warranty
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

http://schema.org/IndividualProduct.label: IndividualProduct
http://schema.org/IndividualProduct.comment: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

properties.label: serialNumber
properties.comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

http://schema.org/OpeningHoursSpecificat.label: OpeningHoursSpecification
http://schema.org/OpeningHoursSpecificat.comment: A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.

properties.label: closes
properties.comment: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

properties.label: dayOfWeek
properties.comment: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

properties.label: opens
properties.comment: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validThrough
properties.comment: The end of the validity of offer, price specification, or opening hours data.

http://schema.org/OwnershipInfo.label: OwnershipInfo
http://schema.org/OwnershipInfo.comment: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

properties.label: acquiredFrom
properties.comment: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

properties.label: ownedFrom
properties.comment: The date and time of obtaining the product.

properties.label: ownedThrough
properties.comment: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

properties.label: typeOfGood
properties.comment: The product that this structured value is referring to.

http://schema.org/ParcelService.label: ParcelService
http://schema.org/ParcelService.comment:
A private parcel service as the delivery mode available for a certain offer.
Commonly used values:

http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

http://schema.org/PaymentChargeSpecifica.label: PaymentChargeSpecification
http://schema.org/PaymentChargeSpecifica.comment: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

properties.label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

properties.label: appliesToPaymentMethod
properties.comment: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

http://schema.org/ProductModel.label: ProductModel
http://schema.org/ProductModel.comment: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

properties.label: isVariantOf
properties.comment: A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.

properties.label: predecessorOf
properties.comment: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

properties.label: successorOf
properties.comment: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

http://schema.org/QualitativeValue.label: QualitativeValue
http://schema.org/QualitativeValue.comment: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type "US" or the garment sizes "S", "M", "L", and "XL".

properties.label: equal
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

properties.label: greater
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

properties.label: greaterOrEqual
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

properties.label: lesser
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

properties.label: lesserOrEqual
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

properties.label: nonEqual
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

properties.label: valueReference
properties.comment: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

properties.label: additionalProperty
properties.comment:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

http://schema.org/QuantitativeValue.label: QuantitativeValue
http://schema.org/QuantitativeValue.comment: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

properties.label: maxValue
properties.comment: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: minValue
properties.comment: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: unitCode
properties.comment: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

properties.label: value
properties.comment: The value of the quantitative value or property value node. For QuantitativeValue, the recommended type for values is 'Number'. For PropertyValue, it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.

properties.label: valueReference
properties.comment: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

properties.label: additionalProperty
properties.comment:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

properties.label: unitText
properties.comment: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

http://schema.org/SomeProducts.label: SomeProducts
http://schema.org/SomeProducts.comment: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

properties.label: inventoryLevel
properties.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

http://schema.org/TypeAndQuantityNode.label: TypeAndQuantityNode
http://schema.org/TypeAndQuantityNode.comment: A structured value indicating the quantity, unit of measurement, and business function of goods included in a bundle offer.

properties.label: amountOfThisGood
properties.comment: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

properties.label: businessFunction
properties.comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

properties.label: typeOfGood
properties.comment: The product that this structured value is referring to.

properties.label: unitCode
properties.comment: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

properties.label: unitText
properties.comment: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

http://schema.org/UnitPriceSpecification.label: UnitPriceSpecification
http://schema.org/UnitPriceSpecification.comment: The price asked for a given offer by the respective organization or person.

properties.label: billingIncrement
properties.comment: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

properties.label: priceType
properties.comment: A short text or acronym indicating multiple price specifications for the same offer, e.g. SRP for the suggested retail price or INVOICE for the invoice price, mostly used in the car industry.

properties.label: unitCode
properties.comment: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

properties.label: unitText
properties.comment: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

http://schema.org/WarrantyPromise.label: WarrantyPromise
http://schema.org/WarrantyPromise.comment: A structured value representing the duration and scope of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

properties.label: durationOfWarranty
properties.comment: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

properties.label: warrantyScope
properties.comment: The scope of the warranty promise.

http://schema.org/WarrantyScope.label: WarrantyScope
http://schema.org/WarrantyScope.comment:
A range of of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.
Commonly used values:

http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Labor-BringIn
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-BringIn
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-PickUp

http://schema.org/TechArticle.label: TechArticle
http://schema.org/TechArticle.comment: A technical article - Example: How-to (task) topics, step-by-step, procedural troubleshooting, specifications, etc.

properties.label: dependencies
properties.comment: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

properties.label: proficiencyLevel
properties.comment: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

http://schema.org/APIReference.label: APIReference
http://schema.org/APIReference.comment: Reference documentation for application programming interfaces (APIs).

properties.label: assembly
properties.comment: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

properties.label: executableLibraryName
properties.comment: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

properties.label: assemblyVersion
properties.comment: Associated product/technology version. e.g., .NET Framework 4.5.

properties.label: programmingModel
properties.comment: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

properties.label: targetPlatform
properties.comment: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

http://schema.org/Code.label: Code
http://schema.org/Code.comment: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

http://schema.org/SoftwareSourceCode.label: SoftwareSourceCode
http://schema.org/SoftwareSourceCode.comment: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

properties.label: codeRepository
properties.comment: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, github, CodePlex).

properties.label: programmingLanguage
properties.comment: The computer programming language.

properties.label: runtime
properties.comment: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (Example - Java v1, Python2.3, .Net Framework 3.0).

properties.label: runtimePlatform
properties.comment: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (Example - Java v1, Python2.3, .Net Framework 3.0).

properties.label: sampleType
properties.comment: What type of sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

properties.label: codeSampleType
properties.comment: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

properties.label: targetProduct
properties.comment: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

http://schema.org/ParentAudience.label: ParentAudience
http://schema.org/ParentAudience.comment: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.

properties.label: childMaxAge
properties.comment: Maximal age of the child.

properties.label: childMinAge
properties.comment: Minimal age of the child.

http://schema.org/AlignmentObject.label: AlignmentObject
http://schema.org/AlignmentObject.comment: An intangible item that describes an alignment between a learning resource and a node in an educational framework.

properties.label: alignmentType
properties.comment: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'assesses', 'teaches', 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', 'educationalSubject', and 'educationLevel'.

properties.label: educationalFramework
properties.comment: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

properties.label: targetDescription
properties.comment: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

properties.label: targetName
properties.comment: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

properties.label: targetUrl
properties.comment: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

properties.label: educationalRole
properties.comment: An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience.

properties.label: dataset
properties.comment: A dataset contained in a catalog.

http://schema.org/Dataset.label: Dataset
http://schema.org/Dataset.comment: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

properties.label: catalog
properties.comment: A data catalog which contains a dataset.

properties.label: includedDataCatalog
properties.comment: A data catalog contained in the dataset.

properties.label: distribution
properties.comment: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.

properties.label: spatial
properties.comment: The range of spatial applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a dataset of New York weather, the state of New York.

properties.label: temporal
properties.comment: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

properties.label: datasetTimeInterval
properties.comment: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

http://schema.org/Class.label: Class
http://schema.org/Class.comment: A class, also often called a 'Type'; equivalent to rdfs:Class.

properties.label: supersededBy
properties.comment: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

http://schema.org/Property.label: Property
http://schema.org/Property.comment: A property, used to indicate attributes and relationships of some Thing; equivalent to rdf:Property.

properties.label: domainIncludes
properties.comment: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

properties.label: inverseOf
properties.comment: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

properties.label: supersededBy
properties.comment: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

properties.label: rangeIncludes
properties.comment: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

http://schema.org/PublicationEvent.label: PublicationEvent
http://schema.org/PublicationEvent.comment: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

properties.label: free
properties.comment: A flag to signal that the publication is accessible for free.

properties.label: isAccessibleForFree
properties.comment: A flag to signal that the publication is accessible for free.

properties.label: publishedOn
properties.comment: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

http://schema.org/BroadcastEvent.label: BroadcastEvent
http://schema.org/BroadcastEvent.comment: An over the air or online broadcast event.

properties.label: videoFormat
properties.comment: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

properties.label: broadcastOfEvent
properties.comment: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

properties.label: isLiveBroadcast
properties.comment: True is the broadcast is of a live event.

http://schema.org/BroadcastService.label: BroadcastService
http://schema.org/BroadcastService.comment: A delivery service through which content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

properties.label: area
properties.comment: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

properties.label: broadcaster
properties.comment: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

properties.label: parentService
properties.comment: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

properties.label: videoFormat
properties.comment: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

properties.label: broadcastAffiliateOf
properties.comment: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

properties.label: broadcastDisplayName
properties.comment: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

properties.label: timezone
properties.comment: The timezone in ISO 8601 format for which the service bases its broadcasts.

http://schema.org/Clip.label: Clip
http://schema.org/Clip.comment: A short TV or radio program or a segment/part of a program.

properties.label: actor
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: actors
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: clipNumber
properties.comment: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

properties.label: director
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: directors
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: musicBy
properties.comment: The composer of the soundtrack.

properties.label: partOfEpisode
properties.comment: The episode to which this clip belongs.

properties.label: partOfSeason
properties.comment: The season to which this episode belongs.

properties.label: partOfSeries
properties.comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

http://schema.org/OnDemandEvent.label: OnDemandEvent
http://schema.org/OnDemandEvent.comment: A publication event e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.

http://schema.org/RadioClip.label: RadioClip
http://schema.org/RadioClip.comment: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.

http://schema.org/RadioEpisode.label: RadioEpisode
http://schema.org/RadioEpisode.comment: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.

http://schema.org/RadioSeason.label: RadioSeason
http://schema.org/RadioSeason.comment: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

http://schema.org/RadioSeries.label: RadioSeries
http://schema.org/RadioSeries.comment: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

properties.label: actor
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: actors
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: director
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: directors
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: episode
properties.comment: An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.

properties.label: episodes
properties.comment: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

properties.label: musicBy
properties.comment: The composer of the soundtrack.

properties.label: numberOfEpisodes
properties.comment: The number of episodes in this season or series.

properties.label: numberOfSeasons
properties.comment: The number of seasons in this series.

properties.label: productionCompany
properties.comment: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

properties.label: productionCompany
properties.comment: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

properties.label: season
properties.comment: A season in a media series.

properties.label: containsSeason
properties.comment: A season that is part of the media series.

properties.label: seasons
properties.comment: A season in a media series.

properties.label: trailer
properties.comment: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

http://schema.org/TVClip.label: TVClip
http://schema.org/TVClip.comment: A short TV program or a segment/part of a TV program.

properties.label: partOfTVSeries
properties.comment: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

http://schema.org/BusinessAudience.label: BusinessAudience
http://schema.org/BusinessAudience.comment: A set of characteristics belonging to businesses, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

properties.label: numberOfEmployees
properties.comment: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

properties.label: yearlyRevenue
properties.comment: The size of the business in annual revenue.

properties.label: yearsInOperation
properties.comment: The age of the business.

http://schema.org/ContactPointOption.label: ContactPointOption
http://schema.org/ContactPointOption.comment: Enumerated options related to a ContactPoint.

http://schema.org/Permit.label: Permit
http://schema.org/Permit.comment: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

properties.label: issuedThrough
properties.comment: The service through with the permit was granted.

properties.label: permitAudience
properties.comment: The target audience for this permit.

properties.label: validFor
properties.comment: The time validity of the permit.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validIn
properties.comment: The geographic area where the permit is valid.

properties.label: validUntil
properties.comment: The date when the item is no longer valid.

properties.label: issuedBy
properties.comment: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

http://schema.org/GovernmentPermit.label: GovernmentPermit
http://schema.org/GovernmentPermit.comment: A permit issued by a government agency.

http://schema.org/Service.label: Service
http://schema.org/Service.comment: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

properties.label: hasOfferCatalog
properties.comment: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: areaServed
properties.comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

properties.label: availableChannel
properties.comment: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

properties.label: award
properties.comment: An award won by or for this item.

properties.label: category
properties.comment: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

properties.label: hoursAvailable
properties.comment: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

properties.label: offers
properties.comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

properties.label: produces
properties.comment: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

properties.label: serviceOutput
properties.comment: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: serviceArea
properties.comment: The geographic area where the service is provided.

properties.label: serviceAudience
properties.comment: The audience eligible for this service.

properties.label: serviceType
properties.comment: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

properties.label: providerMobility
properties.comment: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

http://schema.org/GovernmentService.label: GovernmentService
http://schema.org/GovernmentService.comment: A service provided by a government organization, e.g. food stamps, veterans benefits, etc.

properties.label: serviceOperator
properties.comment: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

http://schema.org/ServiceChannel.label: ServiceChannel
http://schema.org/ServiceChannel.comment: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

properties.label: availableLanguage
properties.comment: A language someone may use with the item.

properties.label: processingTime
properties.comment: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

properties.label: providesService
properties.comment: The service provided by this channel.

properties.label: serviceLocation
properties.comment: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

properties.label: servicePhone
properties.comment: The phone number to use to access the service.

properties.label: servicePostalAddress
properties.comment: The address for accessing the service by mail.

properties.label: serviceSmsNumber
properties.comment: The number to access the service by text message.

properties.label: serviceUrl
properties.comment: The website to access the service.

http://schema.org/EventStatusType.label: EventStatusType
http://schema.org/EventStatusType.comment: EventStatusType is an enumeration type whose instances represent several states that an Event may be in.

http://schema.org/DeliveryEvent.label: DeliveryEvent
http://schema.org/DeliveryEvent.comment: An event involving the delivery of an item.

properties.label: accessCode
properties.comment: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

properties.label: availableFrom
properties.comment: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

properties.label: availableThrough
properties.comment: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

properties.label: hasDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: Method used for delivery or shipping.

http://schema.org/LockerDelivery.label: LockerDelivery
http://schema.org/LockerDelivery.comment: A DeliveryMethod in which an item is made available via locker.

http://schema.org/Order.label: Order
http://schema.org/Order.comment: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

properties.label: orderDelivery
properties.comment: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

properties.label: acceptedOffer
properties.comment: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

properties.label: billingAddress
properties.comment: The billing address for the order.

properties.label: confirmationNumber
properties.comment: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

properties.label: customer
properties.comment: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

properties.label: discount
properties.comment: Any discount applied (to an Order).

properties.label: discountCode
properties.comment: Code used to redeem a discount.

properties.label: discountCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the discount.

properties.label: isGift
properties.comment: Was the offer accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

properties.label: merchant
properties.comment: 'merchant' is an out-dated term for 'seller'.

properties.label: orderDate
properties.comment: Date order was placed.

properties.label: orderedItem
properties.comment: The item ordered.

properties.label: orderNumber
properties.comment: The identifier of the transaction.

properties.label: orderStatus
properties.comment: The current status of the order.

properties.label: partOfInvoice
properties.comment: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

properties.label: paymentDue
properties.comment: The date that payment is due.

properties.label: paymentDueDate
properties.comment: The date that payment is due.

properties.label: paymentMethod
properties.comment: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

properties.label: paymentMethodId
properties.comment: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

properties.label: paymentUrl
properties.comment: The URL for sending a payment.

properties.label: seller
properties.comment: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

properties.label: broker
properties.comment: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

http://schema.org/ParcelDelivery.label: ParcelDelivery
http://schema.org/ParcelDelivery.comment: The delivery of a parcel either via the postal service or a commercial service.

properties.label: carrier
properties.comment: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

properties.label: deliveryAddress
properties.comment: Destination address.

properties.label: deliveryStatus
properties.comment: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

properties.label: expectedArrivalFrom
properties.comment: The earliest date the package may arrive.

properties.label: expectedArrivalUntil
properties.comment: The latest date the package may arrive.

properties.label: hasDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: Method used for delivery or shipping.

properties.label: itemShipped
properties.comment: Item(s) being shipped.

properties.label: originAddress
properties.comment: Shipper's address.

properties.label: partOfOrder
properties.comment: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

properties.label: trackingNumber
properties.comment: Shipper tracking number.

properties.label: trackingUrl
properties.comment: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

http://schema.org/OrderItem.label: OrderItem
http://schema.org/OrderItem.comment: An order item is a line of an order. It includes the quantity and shipping details of a bought offer.

properties.label: orderQuantity
properties.comment: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

properties.label: orderItemStatus
properties.comment: The current status of the order item.

properties.label: orderItemNumber
properties.comment: The identifier of the order item.

properties.label: orderDelivery
properties.comment: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

properties.label: orderedItem
properties.comment: The item ordered.

http://schema.org/Action.label: Action
http://schema.org/Action.comment:
An action performed by a direct agent and indirect participants upon a direct object. Optionally happens at a location with the help of an inanimate instrument. The execution of the action may produce a result. Specific action sub-type documentation specifies the exact expectation of each argument/role.

See also blog post and Actions overview document.

properties.label: agent
properties.comment: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. *John* wrote a book.

properties.label: endTime
properties.comment:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: instrument
properties.comment: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

properties.label: location
properties.comment: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

properties.label: object
properties.comment: The object upon the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read *a book*.

properties.label: participant
properties.comment: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

properties.label: result
properties.comment: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote *a book*.

properties.label: startTime
properties.comment:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: actionStatus
properties.comment: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

properties.label: error
properties.comment: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

properties.label: target
properties.comment: Indicates a target EntryPoint for an Action.

http://schema.org/OrganizeAction.label: OrganizeAction
http://schema.org/OrganizeAction.comment: The act of manipulating/administering/supervising/controlling one or more objects.

http://schema.org/AllocateAction.label: AllocateAction
http://schema.org/AllocateAction.comment: The act of organizing tasks/objects/events by associating resources to it.

properties.label: purpose
properties.comment: A goal towards an action is taken. Can be concrete or abstract.

http://schema.org/AcceptAction.label: AcceptAction
http://schema.org/AcceptAction.comment:
The act of committing to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

  • RejectAction: The antonym of AcceptAction
.

http://schema.org/AchieveAction.label: AchieveAction
http://schema.org/AchieveAction.comment: The act of accomplishing something via previous efforts. It is an instantaneous action rather than an ongoing process.

http://schema.org/UpdateAction.label: UpdateAction
http://schema.org/UpdateAction.comment: The act of managing by changing/editing the state of the object.

properties.label: collection
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

properties.label: targetCollection
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

http://schema.org/AddAction.label: AddAction
http://schema.org/AddAction.comment: The act of editing by adding an object to a collection.

http://schema.org/AssessAction.label: AssessAction
http://schema.org/AssessAction.comment: The act of forming one's opinion, reaction or sentiment.

http://schema.org/ReactAction.label: ReactAction
http://schema.org/ReactAction.comment: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

http://schema.org/AgreeAction.label: AgreeAction
http://schema.org/AgreeAction.comment: The act of expressing a consistency of opinion with the object. An agent agrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

http://schema.org/InsertAction.label: InsertAction
http://schema.org/InsertAction.comment: The act of adding at a specific location in an ordered collection.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

http://schema.org/AppendAction.label: AppendAction
http://schema.org/AppendAction.comment: The act of inserting at the end if an ordered collection.

http://schema.org/ApplyAction.label: ApplyAction
http://schema.org/ApplyAction.comment:
The act of registering to an organization/service without the guarantee to receive it.

Related actions:

  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, ApplyAction has no guarantees that the application will be accepted
.

http://schema.org/MoveAction.label: MoveAction
http://schema.org/MoveAction.comment:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

  • TransferAction: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object
.

properties.label: fromLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

http://schema.org/ArriveAction.label: ArriveAction
http://schema.org/ArriveAction.comment: The act of arriving at a place. An agent arrives at a destination from an fromLocation, optionally with participants.

http://schema.org/InteractAction.label: InteractAction
http://schema.org/InteractAction.comment: The act of interacting with another person or organization.

http://schema.org/CommunicateAction.label: CommunicateAction
http://schema.org/CommunicateAction.comment: The act of conveying information to another person via a communication medium (instrument) such as speech, email, or telephone conversation.

properties.label: about
properties.comment: The subject matter of the content.

properties.label: inLanguage
properties.comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

properties.label: language
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/AskAction.label: AskAction
http://schema.org/AskAction.comment:
The act of posing a question / favor to someone.

Related actions:

  • ReplyAction: Appears generally as a response to AskAction
.

properties.label: question
properties.comment: A sub property of object. A question.

http://schema.org/AssignAction.label: AssignAction
http://schema.org/AssignAction.comment: The act of allocating an action/event/task to some destination (someone or something).

http://schema.org/AuthorizeAction.label: AuthorizeAction
http://schema.org/AuthorizeAction.comment: The act of granting permission to an object.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/BefriendAction.label: BefriendAction
http://schema.org/BefriendAction.comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone (object) mutually/bidirectionally/symmetrically.

Related actions:

  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, BefriendAction implies that the connection is reciprocal
.

http://schema.org/TransferAction.label: TransferAction
http://schema.org/TransferAction.comment: The act of transferring/moving (abstract or concrete) animate or inanimate objects from one place to another.

properties.label: fromLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

http://schema.org/BorrowAction.label: BorrowAction
http://schema.org/BorrowAction.comment:
The act of obtaining an object under an agreement to return it at a later date. Reciprocal of LendAction.

Related actions:

  • LendAction: Reciprocal of BorrowAction
.

properties.label: lender
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

http://schema.org/TradeAction.label: TradeAction
http://schema.org/TradeAction.comment: The act of participating in an exchange of goods and services for monetary compensation. An agent trades an object, product or service with a participant in exchange for a one time or periodic payment.

properties.label: price
properties.comment:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:
  • Use the priceCurrency property (with ISO 4217 codes e.g. "USD") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

properties.label: priceSpecification
properties.comment: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

http://schema.org/BuyAction.label: BuyAction
http://schema.org/BuyAction.comment: The act of giving money to a seller in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent buys an object, product, or service from a seller for a price. Reciprocal of SellAction.

properties.label: seller
properties.comment: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

properties.label: vendor
properties.comment: 'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

properties.label: warrantyPromise
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

http://schema.org/PlanAction.label: PlanAction
http://schema.org/PlanAction.comment: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

properties.label: scheduledTime
properties.comment: The time the object is scheduled to.

http://schema.org/CancelAction.label: CancelAction
http://schema.org/CancelAction.comment:
The act of asserting that a future event/action is no longer going to happen.

Related actions:

  • ConfirmAction: The antonym of CancelAction
.

http://schema.org/FindAction.label: FindAction
http://schema.org/FindAction.comment:
The act of finding an object.

Related actions:

  • SearchAction: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily
.

http://schema.org/CheckAction.label: CheckAction
http://schema.org/CheckAction.comment: An agent inspects/determines/investigates/inquire or examine an object's accuracy/quality/condition or state.

http://schema.org/CheckInAction.label: CheckInAction
http://schema.org/CheckInAction.comment:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their arrival by registering/confirming for a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or at a place (e.g. hotel), possibly resulting in a result (boarding pass, etc).

Related actions:

  • CheckOutAction: The antonym of CheckInAction.
  • ArriveAction: Unlike ArriveAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the start of a previously reserved service.
  • ConfirmAction: Unlike ConfirmAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the *start* of a previously reserved service rather than its validity/existence
.

http://schema.org/CheckOutAction.label: CheckOutAction
http://schema.org/CheckOutAction.comment:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their departure of a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or place (e.g. hotel).

Related actions:

  • CheckInAction: The antonym of CheckOutAction.
  • DepartAction: Unlike DepartAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.
  • CancelAction: Unlike CancelAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service
.

http://schema.org/ChooseAction.label: ChooseAction
http://schema.org/ChooseAction.comment: The act of expressing a preference from a set of options or a large or unbounded set of choices/options.

properties.label: option
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

properties.label: actionOption
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

http://schema.org/CommentAction.label: CommentAction
http://schema.org/CommentAction.comment: The act of generating a comment about a subject.

properties.label: resultComment
properties.comment: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

http://schema.org/InformAction.label: InformAction
