http://schema.org/InformAction.comment: The act of notifying someone of information pertinent to them, with no expectation of a response.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

http://schema.org/ConfirmAction.label: ConfirmAction
http://schema.org/ConfirmAction.comment:
The act of notifying someone that a future event/action is going to happen as expected.

Related actions:

  • CancelAction: The antonym of ConfirmAction
.

properties.label: expectsAcceptanceOf
properties.comment: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

http://schema.org/CreateAction.label: CreateAction
http://schema.org/CreateAction.comment: The act of deliberately creating/producing/generating/building a result out of the agent.

properties.label: foodEstablishment
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

properties.label: foodEvent
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

properties.label: recipe
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

http://schema.org/DeleteAction.label: DeleteAction
http://schema.org/DeleteAction.comment: The act of editing a recipient by removing one of its objects.

http://schema.org/DepartAction.label: DepartAction
http://schema.org/DepartAction.comment: The act of  departing from a place. An agent departs from an fromLocation for a destination, optionally with participants.

http://schema.org/DisagreeAction.label: DisagreeAction
http://schema.org/DisagreeAction.comment: The act of expressing a difference of opinion with the object. An agent disagrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

http://schema.org/DiscoverAction.label: DiscoverAction
http://schema.org/DiscoverAction.comment: The act of discovering/finding an object.

http://schema.org/DislikeAction.label: DislikeAction
http://schema.org/DislikeAction.comment: The act of expressing a negative sentiment about the object. An agent dislikes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

http://schema.org/DonateAction.label: DonateAction
http://schema.org/DonateAction.comment: The act of providing goods, services, or money without compensation, often for philanthropic reasons.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/DownloadAction.label: DownloadAction
http://schema.org/DownloadAction.comment: The act of downloading an object.

http://schema.org/DrawAction.label: DrawAction
http://schema.org/DrawAction.comment: The act of producing a visual/graphical representation of an object, typically with a pen/pencil and paper as instruments.

http://schema.org/EatAction.label: EatAction
http://schema.org/EatAction.comment: The act of swallowing solid objects.

properties.label: endorsee
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

http://schema.org/ControlAction.label: ControlAction
http://schema.org/ControlAction.comment: An agent controls a device or application.

http://schema.org/ActivateAction.label: ActivateAction
http://schema.org/ActivateAction.comment: The act of starting or activating a device or application (e.g. starting a timer or turning on a flashlight).

http://schema.org/DeactivateAction.label: DeactivateAction
http://schema.org/DeactivateAction.comment: The act of stopping or deactivating a device or application (e.g. stopping a timer or turning off a flashlight).

http://schema.org/ResumeAction.label: ResumeAction
http://schema.org/ResumeAction.comment: The act of resuming a device or application which was formerly paused (e.g. resume music playback or resume a timer).

http://schema.org/SuspendAction.label: SuspendAction
http://schema.org/SuspendAction.comment: The act of momentarily pausing a device or application (e.g. pause music playback or pause a timer).

http://schema.org/PlayAction.label: PlayAction
http://schema.org/PlayAction.comment:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, Competition or exercise.

Related actions:

  • ListenAction: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
  • WatchAction: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content
.

properties.label: audience
properties.comment: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

http://schema.org/ExerciseAction.label: ExerciseAction
http://schema.org/ExerciseAction.comment: The act of participating in exertive activity for the purposes of improving health and fitness.

properties.label: course
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

properties.label: exerciseCourse
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

properties.label: diet
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

properties.label: exerciseRelatedDiet
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

properties.label: distance
properties.comment: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

properties.label: exercisePlan
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

properties.label: exerciseType
properties.comment: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

properties.label: fromLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

properties.label: opponent
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

properties.label: sportsActivityLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

properties.label: sportsEvent
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

properties.label: sportsTeam
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

http://schema.org/FilmAction.label: FilmAction
http://schema.org/FilmAction.comment: The act of capturing sound and moving images on film, video, or digitally.

http://schema.org/FollowAction.label: FollowAction
http://schema.org/FollowAction.comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates polled from.

Related actions:

  • BefriendAction: Unlike BefriendAction, FollowAction implies that the connection is *not* necessarily reciprocal.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, FollowAction implies that the follower acts as an active agent constantly/actively polling for updates.
  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in getting updates from the object.
  • TrackAction: Unlike TrackAction, FollowAction refers to the polling of updates of all aspects of animate objects rather than the location of inanimate objects (e.g. you track a package, but you don't follow it)
.

properties.label: followee
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

http://schema.org/GiveAction.label: GiveAction
http://schema.org/GiveAction.comment:
The act of transferring ownership of an object to a destination. Reciprocal of TakeAction.

Related actions:

  • TakeAction: Reciprocal of GiveAction.
  • SendAction: Unlike SendAction, GiveAction implies that ownership is being transferred (e.g. I may send my laptop to you, but that doesn't mean I'm giving it to you)
.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/IgnoreAction.label: IgnoreAction
http://schema.org/IgnoreAction.comment: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.

http://schema.org/InstallAction.label: InstallAction
http://schema.org/InstallAction.comment: The act of installing an application.

http://schema.org/InviteAction.label: InviteAction
http://schema.org/InviteAction.comment: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

http://schema.org/JoinAction.label: JoinAction
http://schema.org/JoinAction.comment:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates
.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

http://schema.org/LeaveAction.label: LeaveAction
http://schema.org/LeaveAction.comment:
An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

  • JoinAction: The antonym of LeaveAction.
  • UnRegisterAction: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service
.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

http://schema.org/LendAction.label: LendAction
http://schema.org/LendAction.comment:
The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Related actions:

  • BorrowAction: Reciprocal of LendAction
.

properties.label: borrower
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

http://schema.org/LikeAction.label: LikeAction
http://schema.org/LikeAction.comment: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

http://schema.org/ListenAction.label: ListenAction
http://schema.org/ListenAction.comment: The act of consuming audio content.

http://schema.org/LoseAction.label: LoseAction
http://schema.org/LoseAction.comment: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.

properties.label: winner
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

http://schema.org/MarryAction.label: MarryAction
http://schema.org/MarryAction.comment: The act of marrying a person.

http://schema.org/OrderAction.label: OrderAction
http://schema.org/OrderAction.comment: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

properties.label: deliveryMethod
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

http://schema.org/PaintAction.label: PaintAction
http://schema.org/PaintAction.comment: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.

http://schema.org/PayAction.label: PayAction
http://schema.org/PayAction.comment: An agent pays a price to a participant.

properties.label: purpose
properties.comment: A goal towards an action is taken. Can be concrete or abstract.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/PerformAction.label: PerformAction
http://schema.org/PerformAction.comment: The act of participating in performance arts.

properties.label: entertainmentBusiness
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

http://schema.org/PhotographAction.label: PhotographAction
http://schema.org/PhotographAction.comment: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.

http://schema.org/PrependAction.label: PrependAction
http://schema.org/PrependAction.comment: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

http://schema.org/QuoteAction.label: QuoteAction
http://schema.org/QuoteAction.comment: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

http://schema.org/ReadAction.label: ReadAction
http://schema.org/ReadAction.comment: The act of consuming written content.

http://schema.org/ReceiveAction.label: ReceiveAction
http://schema.org/ReceiveAction.comment:
The act of physically/electronically taking delivery of an object thathas been transferred from an origin to a destination. Reciprocal of SendAction.

Related actions:

  • SendAction: The reciprocal of ReceiveAction.
  • TakeAction: Unlike TakeAction, ReceiveAction does not imply that the ownership has been transfered (e.g. I can receive a package, but it does not mean the package is now mine)
.

properties.label: deliveryMethod
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

properties.label: sender
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

http://schema.org/RegisterAction.label: RegisterAction
http://schema.org/RegisterAction.comment:
The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.

Related actions:

  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, *not* a group/team of people.
  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object
.

http://schema.org/RejectAction.label: RejectAction
http://schema.org/RejectAction.comment:
The act of rejecting to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

  • AcceptAction: The antonym of RejectAction
.

http://schema.org/RentAction.label: RentAction
http://schema.org/RentAction.comment: The act of giving money in return for temporary use, but not ownership, of an object such as a vehicle or property. For example, an agent rents a property from a landlord in exchange for a periodic payment.

properties.label: landlord
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

properties.label: realEstateAgent
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

http://schema.org/ReplaceAction.label: ReplaceAction
http://schema.org/ReplaceAction.comment: The act of editing a recipient by replacing an old object with a new object.

properties.label: replacee
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

properties.label: replacer
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

http://schema.org/ReplyAction.label: ReplyAction
http://schema.org/ReplyAction.comment:
The act of responding to a question/message asked/sent by the object. Related to AskAction.

Related actions:

  • AskAction: Appears generally as an origin of a ReplyAction
.

properties.label: resultComment
properties.comment: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

http://schema.org/ReserveAction.label: ReserveAction
http://schema.org/ReserveAction.comment:
Reserving a concrete object.

Related actions:

  • ScheduleAction: Unlike ScheduleAction, ReserveAction reserves concrete objects (e.g. a table, a hotel) towards a time slot / spatial allocation
.

http://schema.org/ReturnAction.label: ReturnAction
http://schema.org/ReturnAction.comment: The act of returning to the origin that which was previously received (concrete objects) or taken (ownership).

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/ReviewAction.label: ReviewAction
http://schema.org/ReviewAction.comment: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

properties.label: resultReview
properties.comment: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

http://schema.org/RsvpAction.label: RsvpAction
http://schema.org/RsvpAction.comment: The act of notifying an event organizer as to whether you expect to attend the event.

properties.label: additionalNumberOfGuests
properties.comment: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

properties.label: rsvpResponse
properties.comment: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

properties.label: comment
properties.comment: Comments, typically from users.

http://schema.org/RsvpResponseType.label: RsvpResponseType
http://schema.org/RsvpResponseType.comment: RsvpResponseType is an enumeration type whose instances represent responding to an RSVP request.

http://schema.org/ScheduleAction.label: ScheduleAction
http://schema.org/ScheduleAction.comment:
Scheduling future actions, events, or tasks.

Related actions:

  • ReserveAction: Unlike ReserveAction, ScheduleAction allocates future actions (e.g. an event, a task, etc) towards a time slot / spatial allocation
.

http://schema.org/SearchAction.label: SearchAction
http://schema.org/SearchAction.comment:
The act of searching for an object.

Related actions:

  • FindAction: SearchAction generally leads to a FindAction, but not necessarily
.

properties.label: query
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

http://schema.org/SellAction.label: SellAction
http://schema.org/SellAction.comment: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

properties.label: buyer
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

properties.label: warrantyPromise
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

http://schema.org/SendAction.label: SendAction
http://schema.org/SendAction.comment:
The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination.

Related actions:

  • ReceiveAction: The reciprocal of SendAction.
  • GiveAction: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you)
.

properties.label: deliveryMethod
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/ShareAction.label: ShareAction
http://schema.org/ShareAction.comment: The act of distributing content to people for their amusement or edification.

http://schema.org/SubscribeAction.label: SubscribeAction
http://schema.org/SubscribeAction.comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates pushed to.

Related actions:

  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, SubscribeAction implies that the subscriber acts as a passive agent being constantly/actively pushed for updates.
  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object
.

http://schema.org/TakeAction.label: TakeAction
http://schema.org/TakeAction.comment:
The act of gaining ownership of an object from an origin. Reciprocal of GiveAction.

Related actions:

  • GiveAction: The reciprocal of TakeAction.
  • ReceiveAction: Unlike ReceiveAction, TakeAction implies that ownership has been transfered
.

http://schema.org/TieAction.label: TieAction
http://schema.org/TieAction.comment: The act of reaching a draw in a competitive activity.

http://schema.org/TipAction.label: TipAction
http://schema.org/TipAction.comment: The act of giving money voluntarily to a beneficiary in recognition of services rendered.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

http://schema.org/TrackAction.label: TrackAction
http://schema.org/TrackAction.comment:
An agent tracks an object for updates.

Related actions:

  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimates objects.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimate objects
.

properties.label: deliveryMethod
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

http://schema.org/TravelAction.label: TravelAction
http://schema.org/TravelAction.comment: The act of traveling from an fromLocation to a destination by a specified mode of transport, optionally with participants.

properties.label: distance
properties.comment: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

http://schema.org/UnRegisterAction.label: UnRegisterAction
http://schema.org/UnRegisterAction.comment:
The act of un-registering from a service.

Related actions:

  • RegisterAction: antonym of UnRegisterAction.
  • Leave: Unlike LeaveAction, UnRegisterAction implies that you are unregistering from a service you werer previously registered, rather than leaving a team/group of people
.

http://schema.org/UseAction.label: UseAction
http://schema.org/UseAction.comment: The act of applying an object to its intended purpose.

http://schema.org/ViewAction.label: ViewAction
http://schema.org/ViewAction.comment: The act of consuming static visual content.

http://schema.org/VoteAction.label: VoteAction
http://schema.org/VoteAction.comment: The act of expressing a preference from a fixed/finite/structured set of choices/options.

properties.label: candidate
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

http://schema.org/WantAction.label: WantAction
http://schema.org/WantAction.comment: The act of expressing a desire about the object. An agent wants an object.

http://schema.org/WatchAction.label: WatchAction
http://schema.org/WatchAction.comment: The act of consuming dynamic/moving visual content.

http://schema.org/WearAction.label: WearAction
http://schema.org/WearAction.comment: The act of dressing oneself in clothing.

http://schema.org/WinAction.label: WinAction
http://schema.org/WinAction.comment: The act of achieving victory in a competitive activity.

properties.label: loser
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

http://schema.org/WriteAction.label: WriteAction
http://schema.org/WriteAction.comment: The act of authoring written creative content.

properties.label: inLanguage
properties.comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

properties.label: language
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

http://schema.org/ItemListOrderType.label: ItemListOrderType
http://schema.org/ItemListOrderType.comment: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

http://schema.org/Reservation.label: Reservation
http://schema.org/Reservation.comment: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use http://schema.org/Offer.

properties.label: reservationId
properties.comment: A unique identifier for the reservation.

properties.label: reservationStatus
properties.comment: The current status of the reservation.

properties.label: reservationFor
properties.comment: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant,etc. being reserved.

properties.label: underName
properties.comment: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

properties.label: bookingAgent
properties.comment: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

properties.label: bookingTime
properties.comment: The date and time the reservation was booked.

properties.label: modifiedTime
properties.comment: The date and time the reservation was modified.

properties.label: programMembershipUsed
properties.comment: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

properties.label: reservedTicket
properties.comment: A ticket associated with the reservation.

properties.label: totalPrice
properties.comment: The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

properties.label: priceCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

properties.label: broker
properties.comment: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

http://schema.org/BusReservation.label: BusReservation
http://schema.org/BusReservation.comment: A reservation for bus travel.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

http://schema.org/EventReservation.label: EventReservation
http://schema.org/EventReservation.comment: A reservation for an event like a concert, sporting event, or lecture.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

http://schema.org/FlightReservation.label: FlightReservation
http://schema.org/FlightReservation.comment: A reservation for air travel.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

properties.label: boardingGroup
properties.comment: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

properties.label: passengerSequenceNumber
properties.comment: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

properties.label: securityScreening
properties.comment: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

properties.label: passengerPriorityStatus
properties.comment: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

http://schema.org/FoodEstablishmentReser.label: FoodEstablishmentReservation
http://schema.org/FoodEstablishmentReser.comment: A reservation to dine at a food-related business.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

properties.label: endTime
properties.comment:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: startTime
properties.comment:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: partySize
properties.comment: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

http://schema.org/LodgingReservation.label: LodgingReservation
http://schema.org/LodgingReservation.comment: A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

properties.label: checkinTime
properties.comment: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

properties.label: checkoutTime
properties.comment: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

properties.label: lodgingUnitType
properties.comment: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

properties.label: lodgingUnitDescription
properties.comment: A full description of the lodging unit.

properties.label: numAdults
properties.comment: The number of adults staying in the unit.

properties.label: numChildren
properties.comment: The number of children staying in the unit.

http://schema.org/RentalCarReservation.label: RentalCarReservation
http://schema.org/RentalCarReservation.comment: A reservation for a rental car.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

properties.label: pickupLocation
properties.comment: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

properties.label: dropoffLocation
properties.comment: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

properties.label: pickupTime
properties.comment: When a taxi will pickup a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

properties.label: dropoffTime
properties.comment: When a rental car can be dropped off.

http://schema.org/TaxiReservation.label: TaxiReservation
http://schema.org/TaxiReservation.comment: A reservation for a taxi.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

properties.label: partySize
properties.comment: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

properties.label: pickupLocation
properties.comment: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

properties.label: pickupTime
properties.comment: When a taxi will pickup a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

http://schema.org/TrainReservation.label: TrainReservation
http://schema.org/TrainReservation.comment: A reservation for train travel.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

http://schema.org/ReservationPackage.label: ReservationPackage
http://schema.org/ReservationPackage.comment: A group of multiple reservations with common values for all sub-reservations.

properties.label: subReservation
properties.comment: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

http://schema.org/BusTrip.label: BusTrip
http://schema.org/BusTrip.comment: A trip on a commercial bus line.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

properties.label: departureTime
properties.comment: The expected departure time.

properties.label: arrivalTime
properties.comment: The expected arrival time.

properties.label: busNumber
properties.comment: The unique identifier for the bus.

properties.label: busName
properties.comment: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

properties.label: departureBusStop
properties.comment: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

properties.label: arrivalBusStop
properties.comment: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

http://schema.org/TrainTrip.label: TrainTrip
http://schema.org/TrainTrip.comment: A trip on a commercial train line.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

properties.label: departureTime
properties.comment: The expected departure time.

properties.label: arrivalTime
properties.comment: The expected arrival time.

properties.label: trainNumber
properties.comment: The unique identifier for the train.

properties.label: trainName
properties.comment: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

properties.label: departureStation
properties.comment: The station from which the train departs.

properties.label: arrivalStation
properties.comment: The station where the train trip ends.

properties.label: departurePlatform
properties.comment: The platform from which the train departs.

properties.label: arrivalPlatform
properties.comment: The platform where the train arrives.

properties.label: carrier
properties.comment: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

properties.label: seller
properties.comment: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

properties.label: flightNumber
properties.comment: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

properties.label: departureTime
properties.comment: The expected departure time.

properties.label: arrivalTime
properties.comment: The expected arrival time.

properties.label: departureAirport
properties.comment: The airport where the flight originates.

properties.label: arrivalAirport
properties.comment: The airport where the flight terminates.

properties.label: departureGate
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

properties.label: arrivalGate
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

properties.label: boardingPolicy
properties.comment: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

properties.label: departureTerminal
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

properties.label: arrivalTerminal
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

properties.label: aircraft
properties.comment: The kind of aircraft (e.g., "Boeing 747").

properties.label: mealService
properties.comment: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

properties.label: estimatedFlightDuration
properties.comment: The estimated time the flight will take.

properties.label: flightDistance
properties.comment: The distance of the flight.

properties.label: webCheckinTime
properties.comment: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

http://schema.org/Airline.label: Airline
http://schema.org/Airline.comment: An organization that provides flights for passengers.

properties.label: boardingPolicy
properties.comment: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

properties.label: iataCode
properties.comment: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

http://schema.org/ProgramMembership.label: ProgramMembership
http://schema.org/ProgramMembership.comment: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. "StarAliance"), traveler clubs (e.g. "AAA"), purchase clubs ("Safeway Club"), etc.

properties.label: member
properties.comment: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

properties.label: members
properties.comment: A member of this organization.

properties.label: membershipNumber
properties.comment: A unique identifier for the membership.

properties.label: programName
properties.comment: The program providing the membership.

properties.label: hostingOrganization
properties.comment: The organization (airline, travelers' club, etc.) the membership is made with.

http://schema.org/Ticket.label: Ticket
http://schema.org/Ticket.comment: Used to describe a ticket to an event, a flight, a bus ride, etc.

properties.label: underName
properties.comment: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

properties.label: totalPrice
properties.comment: The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

properties.label: priceCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

properties.label: issuedBy
properties.comment: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

properties.label: dateIssued
properties.comment: The date the ticket was issued.

properties.label: ticketedSeat
properties.comment: The seat associated with the ticket.

properties.label: ticketNumber
properties.comment: The unique identifier for the ticket.

properties.label: ticketToken
properties.comment: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

http://schema.org/Seat.label: Seat
http://schema.org/Seat.comment: Used to describe a seat, such as a reserved seat in an event reservation.

properties.label: seatNumber
properties.comment: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

properties.label: seatRow
properties.comment: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

properties.label: seatSection
properties.comment: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

properties.label: seatingType
properties.comment: The type/class of the seat.

http://schema.org/TaxiService.label: TaxiService
http://schema.org/TaxiService.comment: A service for a vehicle for hire with a driver for local travel. Fares are usually calculated based on distance traveled.

http://schema.org/Vehicle.label: Vehicle
http://schema.org/Vehicle.comment: A vehicle is a device that is designed or used to transport people or cargo over land, water, air, or through space.

properties.label: numberOfDoors
properties.comment:
The number of doors.
Typical unit code(s): C62

properties.label: numberOfAirbags
properties.comment: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

properties.label: numberOfAxles
properties.comment:
The number of axles.
Typical unit code(s): C62

properties.label: vehicleEngine
properties.comment: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

properties.label: fuelConsumption
properties.comment:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).
Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.
Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km. Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

properties.label: fuelEfficiency
properties.comment:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).
Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter.
Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L. Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

properties.label: numberOfForwardGears
properties.comment:
The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.
Typical unit code(s): C62

properties.label: vin
properties.comment: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

properties.label: cargoVolume
properties.comment:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.
Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet
Note: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

properties.label: vehicleConfiguration
properties.comment: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

properties.label: knownVehicleDamages
properties.comment: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

properties.label: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
properties.comment: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

properties.label: driveWheelConfiguration
properties.comment: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

properties.label: fuelType
properties.comment: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

properties.label: vehicleInteriorColor
properties.comment: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

properties.label: vehicleInteriorType
properties.comment: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

properties.label: mileageFromOdometer
properties.comment:
The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.
Typical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

properties.label: vehicleModelDate
properties.comment: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

properties.label: numberOfPreviousOwners
properties.comment:
The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.
Typical unit code(s): C62

properties.label: productionDate
properties.comment: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

properties.label: purchaseDate
properties.comment: The date the item e.g. vehicle was purchased by the current owner.

properties.label: vehicleSeatingCapacity
properties.comment:
The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.
Typical unit code(s): C62 for persons

properties.label: vehicleTransmission
properties.comment: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

properties.label: steeringPosition
properties.comment: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

http://schema.org/Car.label: Car
http://schema.org/Car.comment: A car is a wheeled, self-powered motor vehicle used for transportation.

http://schema.org/BoardingPolicyType.label: BoardingPolicyType
http://schema.org/BoardingPolicyType.comment: A type of boarding policy used by an airline.

http://schema.org/QAPage.label: QAPage
http://schema.org/QAPage.comment: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).

http://schema.org/Question.label: Question
http://schema.org/Question.comment: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

properties.label: upvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

properties.label: downvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

properties.label: answerCount
properties.comment: The number of answers this question has received.

properties.label: acceptedAnswer
properties.comment: The answer that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

properties.label: suggestedAnswer
properties.comment: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

http://schema.org/Answer.label: Answer
http://schema.org/Answer.comment: An answer offered to a question; perhaps correct, perhaps opinionated or wrong.

http://schema.org/EntryPoint.label: EntryPoint
http://schema.org/EntryPoint.comment: An entry point, within some Web-based protocol.

properties.label: actionPlatform
properties.comment: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

properties.label: httpMethod
properties.comment: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

properties.label: encodingType
properties.comment: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

properties.label: contentType
properties.comment: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

properties.label: application
properties.comment: An application that can complete the request.

properties.label: actionApplication
properties.comment: An application that can complete the request.

properties.label: urlTemplate
properties.comment: A url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

properties.label: maxValue
properties.comment: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: minValue
properties.comment: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: valueName
properties.comment: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

properties.label: valueRequired
properties.comment: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

properties.label: defaultValue
properties.comment: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

properties.label: readonlyValue
properties.comment: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

properties.label: multipleValues
properties.comment: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

properties.label: valueMinLength
properties.comment: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

properties.label: valueMaxLength
properties.comment: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

properties.label: valuePattern
properties.comment: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

properties.label: stepValue
properties.comment: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

http://schema.org/Role.label: Role
http://schema.org/Role.comment:
Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.

See also blog post.

properties.label: endDate
properties.comment: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

properties.label: startDate
properties.comment: The start date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

properties.label: namedPosition
properties.comment: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

properties.label: roleName
properties.comment: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

http://schema.org/PerformanceRole.label: PerformanceRole
http://schema.org/PerformanceRole.comment: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.

properties.label: characterName
properties.comment: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

http://schema.org/OrganizationRole.label: OrganizationRole
http://schema.org/OrganizationRole.comment: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.

properties.label: numberedPosition
properties.comment: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

http://schema.org/EmployeeRole.label: EmployeeRole
http://schema.org/EmployeeRole.comment: A subclass of OrganizationRole used to describe employee relationships.

properties.label: baseSalary
properties.comment: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

properties.label: salaryCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (coded using ISO 4217, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217 ) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

http://schema.org/WebSite.label: WebSite
http://schema.org/WebSite.comment: A WebSite is a set of related web pages and other items typically served from a single web domain and accessible via URLs.

http://schema.org/Periodical.label: Periodical
http://schema.org/Periodical.comment:
A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper to continue indefinitely.

See also blog post.

properties.label: issn
properties.comment: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this periodical. You can repeat this property to (for example) identify different formats of this periodical.

http://schema.org/PublicationVolume.label: PublicationVolume
http://schema.org/PublicationVolume.comment:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.

See also blog post.

properties.label: pageEnd
properties.comment: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

properties.label: pageStart
properties.comment: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

properties.label: pagination
properties.comment: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

properties.label: volumeNumber
properties.comment: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

http://schema.org/PublicationIssue.label: PublicationIssue
http://schema.org/PublicationIssue.comment:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.

See also blog post.

properties.label: issueNumber
properties.comment: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

properties.label: pageEnd
properties.comment: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

properties.label: pageStart
properties.comment: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

properties.label: pagination
properties.comment: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

http://schema.org/ListItem.label: ListItem
http://schema.org/ListItem.comment: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.

properties.label: position
properties.comment: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

properties.label: item
properties.comment: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

properties.label: previousItem
properties.comment: A link to the ListItem that preceeds the current one.

properties.label: nextItem
properties.comment: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

http://schema.org/MovieSeries.label: MovieSeries
http://schema.org/MovieSeries.comment: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

properties.label: actor
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: actors
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: director
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: directors
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: musicBy
properties.comment: The composer of the soundtrack.

properties.label: productionCompany
properties.comment: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

properties.label: trailer
properties.comment: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

http://schema.org/BookSeries.label: BookSeries
http://schema.org/BookSeries.comment: A series of books. Included books can be indicated with the hasPart property.

http://schema.org/VideoGame.label: VideoGame
http://schema.org/VideoGame.comment: A video game is an electronic game that involves human interaction with a user interface to generate visual feedback on a video device.

properties.label: actor
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: actors
properties.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: director
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: directors
properties.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

properties.label: musicBy
properties.comment: The composer of the soundtrack.

properties.label: trailer
properties.comment: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

properties.label: playMode
properties.comment: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

properties.label: cheatCode
properties.comment: Cheat codes to the game.

properties.label: gameTip
properties.comment: Links to tips, tactics, etc.

properties.label: gamePlatform
properties.comment: The electronic systems used to play video games.

properties.label: gameServer
properties.comment: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

http://schema.org/VideoGameClip.label: VideoGameClip
http://schema.org/VideoGameClip.comment: A short segment/part of a video game.

http://schema.org/GameServer.label: GameServer
http://schema.org/GameServer.comment: Server that provides game interaction in a multiplayer game.

properties.label: serverStatus
properties.comment: Status of a game server.

properties.label: playersOnline
properties.comment: Number of players on the server.

properties.label: game
properties.comment: Video game which is played on this server.

http://schema.org/Game.label: Game
http://schema.org/Game.comment: The Game type represents things which are games. These are typically rule-governed recreational activities, e.g. role-playing games in which players assume the role of characters in a fictional setting. See also open issues list.

properties.label: numberOfPlayers
properties.comment: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

properties.label: quest
properties.comment: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

properties.label: gameItem
properties.comment: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

properties.label: characterAttribute
properties.comment: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

properties.label: gameLocation
properties.comment: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

http://schema.org/GamePlayMode.label: GamePlayMode
http://schema.org/GamePlayMode.comment: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.

http://schema.org/MusicAlbumProductionTy.label: MusicAlbumProductionType
http://schema.org/MusicAlbumProductionTy.comment: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

http://schema.org/MusicAlbumReleaseType.label: MusicAlbumReleaseType
http://schema.org/MusicAlbumReleaseType.comment: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

properties.label: musicArrangement
properties.comment: An arrangement derived from the composition.

properties.label: composer
properties.comment: The person or organization who wrote the composition.

properties.label: firstPerformance
properties.comment: The date and place the work was first performed.

properties.label: includedComposition
properties.comment: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

properties.label: iswcCode
properties.comment: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

properties.label: lyricist
properties.comment: The person who wrote the words.

properties.label: lyrics
properties.comment: The words in the song.

properties.label: musicCompositionForm
properties.comment: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

properties.label: musicalKey
properties.comment: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

properties.label: recordedAs
properties.comment: An audio recording of the work.

http://schema.org/MusicRelease.label: MusicRelease
http://schema.org/MusicRelease.comment: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

properties.label: catalogNumber
properties.comment: The catalog number for the release.

properties.label: creditedTo
properties.comment: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

properties.label: musicReleaseFormat
properties.comment: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

properties.label: recordLabel
properties.comment: The label that issued the release.

properties.label: releaseOf
properties.comment: The album this is a release of.

http://schema.org/MusicReleaseFormatType.label: MusicReleaseFormatType
http://schema.org/MusicReleaseFormatType.comment: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

http://schema.org/SportsOrganization.label: SportsOrganization
http://schema.org/SportsOrganization.comment: Represents the collection of all sports organizations, including sports teams, governing bodies, and sports associations.

properties.label: sport
properties.comment: A type of sport (e.g. Baseball).

http://schema.org/DatedMoneySpecificatio.label: DatedMoneySpecification
http://schema.org/DatedMoneySpecificatio.comment: A DatedMoneySpecification represents monetary values with optional start and end dates. For example, this could represent an employee's salary over a specific period of time.

properties.label: amount
properties.comment: The amount of money.

properties.label: currency
properties.comment: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format).

http://schema.org/VisualArtwork.label: VisualArtwork
http://schema.org/VisualArtwork.comment: A work of art that is primarily visual in character.

properties.label: artform
properties.comment: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

properties.label: material
properties.comment: e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.

properties.label: artMedium
properties.comment: The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

properties.label: surface
properties.comment: e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

properties.label: artworkSurface
properties.comment: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

properties.label: artEdition
properties.comment: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

http://schema.org/Invoice.label: Invoice
http://schema.org/Invoice.comment: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.

properties.label: category
properties.comment: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

properties.label: confirmationNumber
properties.comment: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

properties.label: customer
properties.comment: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

properties.label: paymentDue
properties.comment: The date that payment is due.

properties.label: paymentDueDate
properties.comment: The date that payment is due.

properties.label: paymentMethod
properties.comment: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

properties.label: paymentMethodId
properties.comment: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

properties.label: broker
properties.comment: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

properties.label: totalPaymentDue
properties.comment: The total amount due.

properties.label: minimumPaymentDue
properties.comment: The minimum payment required at this time.

properties.label: accountId
properties.comment: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

properties.label: scheduledPaymentDate
properties.comment: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

properties.label: billingPeriod
properties.comment: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

properties.label: paymentStatus
properties.comment: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

properties.label: referencesOrder
properties.comment: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

http://schema.org/PaymentStatusType.label: PaymentStatusType
http://schema.org/PaymentStatusType.comment: A specific payment status. For example, PaymentDue, PaymentComplete, etc.

http://schema.org/PropertyValue.label: PropertyValue
http://schema.org/PropertyValue.comment:
A property-value pair, e.g. representing a feature of a product or place. Use the 'name' property for the name of the property. If there is an additional human-readable version of the value, put that into the 'description' property.

Always use specific schema.org properties when a) they exist and b) you can populate them. Using PropertyValue as a substitute will typically not trigger the same effect as using the original, specific property.

properties.label: maxValue
properties.comment: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: minValue
properties.comment: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: unitCode
properties.comment: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

properties.label: value
properties.comment: The value of the quantitative value or property value node. For QuantitativeValue, the recommended type for values is 'Number'. For PropertyValue, it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.

properties.label: valueReference
properties.comment: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

properties.label: unitText
properties.comment: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

properties.label: propertyID
properties.comment:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

http://schema.org/CableOrSatelliteServic.label: CableOrSatelliteService
http://schema.org/CableOrSatelliteServic.comment: A service which provides access to media programming like TV or radio. Access may be via cable or satellite.

http://schema.org/BroadcastChannel.label: BroadcastChannel
http://schema.org/BroadcastChannel.comment: A unique instance of a BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

properties.label: broadcastChannelId
properties.comment: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

properties.label: inBroadcastLineup
properties.comment: The CableOrSatelliteService offering the channel.

properties.label: broadcastServiceTier
properties.comment: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

properties.label: providesBroadcastService
properties.comment: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

http://schema.org/TelevisionChannel.label: TelevisionChannel
http://schema.org/TelevisionChannel.comment: A unique instance of a television BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

http://schema.org/RadioChannel.label: RadioChannel
http://schema.org/RadioChannel.comment: A unique instance of a radio BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

http://schema.org/EngineSpecification.label: EngineSpecification
http://schema.org/EngineSpecification.comment: Information about the engine of the vehicle. A vehicle can have multiple engines represented by multiple engine specification entities.

properties.label: fuelType
properties.comment: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

http://schema.org/DriveWheelConfiguratio.label: DriveWheelConfigurationValue
http://schema.org/DriveWheelConfiguratio.comment: A value indicating which roadwheels will receive torque.

http://schema.org/SteeringPositionValue.label: SteeringPositionValue
http://schema.org/SteeringPositionValue.comment: A value indicating a steering position.

http://schema.org/CarUsageType.label: CarUsageType
http://schema.org/CarUsageType.comment: A value indicating a special usage of a car, e.g. commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi.

http://schema.org/InteractionCounter.label: InteractionCounter
http://schema.org/InteractionCounter.comment: A summary of how users have interacted with this CreativeWork. In most cases, authors will use a subtype to specify the specific type of interaction.

properties.label: interactionService
properties.comment: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

properties.label: interactionType
properties.comment: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use LikeAction. For down votes use DislikeAction. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

properties.label: userInteractionCount
properties.comment: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

http://schema.org/SocialMediaPosting.label: SocialMediaPosting
http://schema.org/SocialMediaPosting.comment: A post to a social media platform, including blog posts, tweets, Facebook posts, etc.

properties.label: sharedContent
properties.comment: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

http://schema.org/DiscussionForumPosting.label: DiscussionForumPosting
http://schema.org/DiscussionForumPosting.comment: A posting to a discussion forum.

http://schema.org/LiveBlogPosting.label: LiveBlog
http://schema.org/LiveBlogPosting.comment: A blog post intended to provide a rolling textual coverage of an ongoing event through continuous updates.

properties.label: coverageStartTime
properties.comment: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

properties.label: coverageEndTime
properties.comment: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

properties.label: liveBlogUpdate
properties.comment: An update to the LiveBlog.

http://schema.org/DataFeed.label: DataFeed
http://schema.org/DataFeed.comment: A single feed providing structured information about one or more entities or topics.

properties.label: dataFeedElement
properties.comment: An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

http://schema.org/DataFeedItem.label: DataFeedItem
http://schema.org/DataFeedItem.comment: A single item within a larger data feed.

properties.label: dateCreated
properties.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

properties.label: dateDeleted
properties.comment: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

properties.label: dateModified
properties.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

properties.label: item
properties.comment: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').
